<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

05:07.308 --> 05:08.840
<i> [WHISTLES A COMMAND]</i>

05:10.744 --> 05:14.813
<i> [GUNFIRE IN DISTANCE]</i>

05:14.815 --> 05:20.052
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

05:20.054 --> 05:24.423
JOHN BREAKER:<i> "Dear Bonnie,</i>
today marks four years.

05:24.425 --> 05:26.391
<i> Four years of fightin'.</i>

05:26.393 --> 05:28.927
<i> Feels like 400.</i>

05:28.929 --> 05:34.099
<i> At the time of this letter,</i>
our son's still safe and well.

05:34.101 --> 05:37.002
<i> As well as can be expected.</i>

05:37.004 --> 05:40.572
<i> He's become close with</i>
Virgil's boy, Perkins.

05:40.574 --> 05:42.874
<i> I know you don't</i>
approve of "The Saint"

05:42.876 --> 05:44.943
<i> as we've come to call him.</i>

05:44.945 --> 05:47.412
Let's go.<i> Ironic, I know.</i>

05:47.414 --> 05:49.348
<i> But his son is a good kid.</i>

05:50.951 --> 05:55.120
<i> When I get back-</i>
When we get back...

05:55.122 --> 05:57.422
<i> We'll have stories</i>
to tell, Bonnie girl.

05:57.424 --> 06:02.728
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

06:02.730 --> 06:09.968
<i> ¶ ["THE WARRANT" THEME] ¶</i>

06:09.970 --> 06:17.709
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

06:18.846 --> 06:20.779
<i> [DOOR CLOSES]</i>

06:20.781 --> 06:22.614
No joy?

06:22.616 --> 06:23.982
He won't check his gun
and he won't tell me

06:23.984 --> 06:26.418
why he's here.

06:26.420 --> 06:28.387
JOHN: Boar headed bounty hunter.

06:28.389 --> 06:30.155
I'll go in and get him out.

06:30.157 --> 06:32.758
You know what
happened last time.

06:32.760 --> 06:35.560
<i> Assault and battery,</i>
aggravated assault, attempt to-

06:35.562 --> 06:36.928
Well what about him?

06:36.930 --> 06:38.997
Murderin', robbin',
horse thievin'.

06:38.999 --> 06:40.732
BUGLE:<i> Be careful</i>
is all I'm sayin'.

06:40.734 --> 06:42.567
Careful?

06:42.569 --> 06:44.102
All these years we've
been ridin' together,

06:44.104 --> 06:45.637
I've never heard you talk like-

06:45.639 --> 06:47.806
Don't get all mushy
on me, Sheriff.

06:47.808 --> 06:49.641
I ain't talkin'
about your health.

06:49.643 --> 06:52.911
I'm thinkin' about
your job, my job.

06:52.913 --> 06:54.679
Just because some black-eyed...

06:54.681 --> 06:56.081
Black-eyed?

06:56.083 --> 06:57.783
Bloody-nosed jay hawker...

06:57.785 --> 06:59.818
Bloody-nosed?

06:59.820 --> 07:01.920
Jack Swanson came at me
with a blade and weren't

07:01.922 --> 07:05.824
no butter-knife neither. Break,
you used a fence-post on him.

07:05.826 --> 07:08.427
He had more than a black
eye and a bloody nose.

07:08.429 --> 07:09.928
What was I supposed to
do, let him stick me?

07:09.930 --> 07:12.464
Tread gently is all.

07:12.466 --> 07:16.435
Bonnie said you had it in you,
lands and lovers and such.

07:16.437 --> 07:18.570
<i> [EXHALES SLOWLY]</i>

07:18.572 --> 07:21.673
And such.

07:21.675 --> 07:23.508
You go around the back just
in case he makes a run for

07:23.510 --> 07:24.843
it when the tickling starts.

07:24.845 --> 07:26.778
BUGLE: The tickling ain't
what makes me nervous.

07:26.780 --> 07:28.847
Well, it should!
<i> [KICKS DOOR OPEN]</i>

07:28.849 --> 07:32.017
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

07:32.019 --> 07:34.186
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

07:34.188 --> 07:36.555
JOHN: Hello Bobby.<i> [GROANS]</i>

07:36.557 --> 07:38.557
<i> [PUNCHES]</i> BOBBY: Your mama
teach ya how to fight?

07:39.993 --> 07:41.993
JOHN: Don't you
talk about my mama!

07:41.995 --> 07:43.795
<i> [GRUNTING]</i>

07:43.797 --> 07:45.096
<i> [GROANS]</i>

07:45.098 --> 07:46.465
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

07:46.467 --> 07:47.499
<i> What?</i>

07:47.501 --> 07:48.867
He insulted my mother.

07:48.869 --> 07:50.735
<i>You</i> didn't even know your mama.

07:50.737 --> 07:53.572
All the more, Buge,
all the more.

07:54.575 --> 07:57.142
<i> [GRUNTS]</i>

07:57.144 --> 07:59.211
Who sent ya?

07:59.213 --> 08:01.646
Nobody.

08:01.648 --> 08:02.714
Never heard of him.

08:02.716 --> 08:03.949
You ever heard of him?

08:03.951 --> 08:06.485
<i> A Mr. Nobody.</i> Hard to say.

08:06.487 --> 08:09.087
Oh heck, Buge, they say you're
the brains of the outfit.

08:09.089 --> 08:11.022
I thought I was the looks.

08:12.893 --> 08:14.259
Up!

08:14.261 --> 08:16.228
<i> [BOTH GRUNTING]</i>

08:16.230 --> 08:19.564
You are the third
tight-lipped bounty-hunter

08:19.566 --> 08:21.099
we've had to move
out this month.

08:21.101 --> 08:22.701
<i> [GRUNT]</i>

08:22.703 --> 08:24.169
There's something
cookin' around here Buge.

08:24.171 --> 08:26.505
And it's making me hangry.

08:26.507 --> 08:28.773
<i> [KICK] [GRUNT]</i>

08:28.775 --> 08:31.176
BLACKJACK:<i> You heard</i>
that carpetbagger.

08:31.178 --> 08:34.246
He's offering good,
hard coin for The Saint.

08:34.248 --> 08:35.747
Dead or alive.

08:35.749 --> 08:37.215
Where's the Union now?

08:37.217 --> 08:38.984
Where's their promises?

08:38.986 --> 08:42.220
They ripped our world apart!

08:42.222 --> 08:44.189
Where's their promise of mercy?

08:44.191 --> 08:46.958
The Saint's been
stealin' those promises.

08:46.960 --> 08:49.995
Breakin' it while they sit
back gettin' fat on victory.

08:49.997 --> 08:52.163
My farm's in ashes.

08:52.165 --> 08:54.132
My kids is hungry.

08:54.134 --> 08:56.568
The Union's failed us again.

08:56.570 --> 08:58.270
It's on us, to take what's ours.

08:58.272 --> 09:00.005
CAL BREAKER: Are you boys
talkin' about The Saint?

09:00.007 --> 09:02.974
<i> ¶ [SUSPENSE] ¶</i>

09:02.976 --> 09:04.910
What's it to ya?

09:04.912 --> 09:08.980
Well, a friendly piece of
advice, I would stay clear.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.582
<i> Let the law work for ya.</i>

09:10.584 --> 09:12.017
Not against ya.

09:12.019 --> 09:14.085
The law ain't feedin' my family!

09:15.889 --> 09:18.123
Neither are you, if you're<i> dead.</i>

09:18.125 --> 09:19.324
What'd you say?

09:19.326 --> 09:20.859
<i> [COCKING GUNS]</i>

09:20.861 --> 09:22.761
Is that a threat boy?!

09:22.763 --> 09:24.963
Come on down here and face us
like a man or I'll shoot you-

09:24.965 --> 09:28.767
I'd lower that hammer
before I drop mine.

09:28.769 --> 09:31.770
Uh-uh. DEPUTY SHANKS:<i> You heard</i>
the deputy marshal, now drop it.

09:31.772 --> 09:35.574
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

09:35.576 --> 09:43.648
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

09:43.650 --> 09:46.651
Steer clear, boys,
you've been warned.

09:46.653 --> 09:53.892
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

09:53.894 --> 09:56.127
CAL:<i> Jeremiah.</i>

09:56.129 --> 09:58.029
JEREMIAH:<i> Stay safe, fellas.</i>

09:58.031 --> 10:06.104
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

10:08.041 --> 10:16.114
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

10:17.884 --> 10:25.957
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

10:30.330 --> 10:36.635
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA] ¶</i>

10:36.637 --> 10:38.370
No.

10:38.372 --> 10:43.141
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA PLAYING] ¶</i>

10:43.143 --> 10:44.809
Hmph.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.811
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA PLAYING] ¶</i>

10:48.281 --> 10:51.950
No.<i> [LAUGHING]</i>
It's more like this.

10:51.952 --> 10:59.257
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA] ¶</i>

10:59.259 --> 11:02.027
My son never had many friends.

11:02.029 --> 11:04.929
War will make 'em brothers
before it's all over.

11:07.401 --> 11:09.668
Want any of this?

11:09.670 --> 11:11.302
Got it off a Georgia boy.

11:11.304 --> 11:14.773
I don't suppose that
was an even trade?

11:14.775 --> 11:16.441
Spoils of war,<i> brother.</i>

11:20.781 --> 11:22.447
John? Hmm?

11:24.685 --> 11:27.419
THE SAINT: I've seen you stare
down a bear with only a round

11:27.421 --> 11:29.120
<i> left in your chamber.</i>

11:29.122 --> 11:31.456
I've seen you crack more
skulls and break more bones

11:31.458 --> 11:32.957
than any man in the territory.

11:32.959 --> 11:34.292
I mean, you're as
tough as they come.

11:34.294 --> 11:38.363
But when it comes to
these gray backs...

11:38.365 --> 11:40.131
your sympathy concerns me.

11:42.269 --> 11:43.868
Well...

11:43.870 --> 11:46.771
that bear had it coming,
he killed my dog.

11:46.773 --> 11:49.007
As for cracking and breaking
something, I'd rather

11:49.009 --> 11:52.444
put something in a sling
than in a grave.

11:52.446 --> 11:55.113
As for them...

11:55.115 --> 11:57.949
I believe in what
we're fighting for.

11:57.951 --> 12:00.852
Doesn't mean I have to hate
who I'm fighting against.

12:00.854 --> 12:02.187
Mm.

12:02.189 --> 12:05.356
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA] ¶</i>

12:05.358 --> 12:07.459
<i> [CHUCKLING]</i> Sound any good?

12:07.461 --> 12:08.927
Yeah.

12:08.929 --> 12:10.128
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA] ¶</i>

12:10.130 --> 12:12.397
Keep it simple.

12:12.399 --> 12:15.233
Good guys in blue,
bad guys in gray.

12:15.235 --> 12:17.736
Well, that's not how I see it.

12:17.738 --> 12:22.240
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

12:22.242 --> 12:24.109
When this is over...

12:24.111 --> 12:27.312
If Davis and Lee and the rest
of these guys aren't dancing

12:27.314 --> 12:29.314
at the end of a rope...

12:29.316 --> 12:32.784
I'm gonna pay old Honest
Abe a visit myself.

12:32.786 --> 12:35.487
That talk brings trouble, Virg.

12:35.489 --> 12:37.255
Trouble can find me.

12:37.257 --> 12:45.296
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

12:46.900 --> 12:48.066
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

12:48.068 --> 12:52.871
<i> [CHICKEN CLUCKING]</i>

12:52.873 --> 12:56.875
<i> [CHOPPING WOOD]</i>

12:56.877 --> 12:59.511
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

12:59.513 --> 13:01.412
BONNIE:<i> John?</i>

13:01.414 --> 13:05.416
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

13:05.418 --> 13:06.551
You make 'em out?

13:06.553 --> 13:11.556
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

13:11.558 --> 13:13.925
Too far. Oh.

13:13.927 --> 13:16.027
It's the marshal.

13:16.029 --> 13:19.030
Guess he heard
about the fence post.

13:19.032 --> 13:20.431
Fence post?

13:20.433 --> 13:22.066
<i> [CLEARS THROAT]</i>
You sure it's him?

13:22.068 --> 13:23.368
Of course, I'm sure.

13:23.370 --> 13:25.937
Look at how he sits
in that saddle.

13:25.939 --> 13:27.806
He rides like you.

13:27.808 --> 13:29.974
I look that good?

13:29.976 --> 13:33.244
What's that on his head?

13:33.246 --> 13:35.079
Is that a new hat?

13:35.081 --> 13:37.916
And a new deputy.

13:37.918 --> 13:41.085
Huh...

13:41.087 --> 13:44.255
How do you do, marshal?

13:44.257 --> 13:45.957
Mom, Sheriff.

13:45.959 --> 13:47.559
This is Deputy Shanks.

13:47.561 --> 13:49.294
Afternoon, ma'am.

13:49.296 --> 13:51.296
Deputy Shanks, call me Bonnie.

13:51.298 --> 13:53.097
It's a pleasure.<i> [CLEARS THROAT]</i>

13:54.334 --> 13:57.068
And this is Sheriff Breaker.

13:57.070 --> 13:59.971
His<i> daddy.</i>

13:59.973 --> 14:02.240
<i> [LAUGHS]</i>
Well, it's an honor, Sheriff.

14:02.242 --> 14:04.042
Shanks.

14:04.044 --> 14:06.377
You wouldn't happen to be kin
to a Colonel Williford Shanks,

14:06.379 --> 14:07.946
would ya?

14:07.948 --> 14:10.215
Yes sir, that's my daddy.

14:10.217 --> 14:12.183
You're Willy's boy!

14:12.185 --> 14:14.052
I'll be.

14:14.054 --> 14:16.554
How is old guts n' glory doing?

14:16.556 --> 14:19.591
Uh, well...

14:19.593 --> 14:21.960
He actually passed
last spring sir.

14:21.962 --> 14:23.895
<i> Caught pneumonia.</i>

14:23.897 --> 14:26.331
<i> But he told me plenty</i>
of stories about you.

14:26.333 --> 14:28.266
<i> Mostly from the war.</i>

14:28.268 --> 14:30.401
He was a good man.

14:30.403 --> 14:32.303
<i> You look a lot like him.</i>

14:32.305 --> 14:34.439
Thank you, sir.

14:34.441 --> 14:36.241
Bugle.

14:36.243 --> 14:39.043
Marshal.

14:39.045 --> 14:40.345
You boys hungry?

14:40.347 --> 14:42.113
Can I put on a chicken? M'm...

14:42.115 --> 14:43.915
CAL:<i> You've slaughtered enough</i>
chickens on my account.

14:43.917 --> 14:45.650
Whatever the Sheriff's
having, that'd be fine.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.151
No, no, no; Those
chickens have been

14:47.153 --> 14:48.620
thrivin' under my
shadow too long.

14:48.622 --> 14:50.521
The only time I get a
treat is when you show up.

14:50.523 --> 14:52.490
Bonnie, slaughter
the fatted hen.

14:52.492 --> 14:54.559
The prodigal has returned.

14:54.561 --> 14:56.561
<i> Fried</i> chicken, then.

14:56.563 --> 14:58.363
M'm.

15:00.133 --> 15:02.967
<i> [CLEARS THROAT]</i>

15:02.969 --> 15:06.204
I uh... suppose you heard
about the whole fence post

15:06.206 --> 15:08.039
thing and Jack Swanson and all?

15:08.041 --> 15:09.574
I did.

15:09.576 --> 15:10.642
JOHN: And I suppose
that's why you're here.

15:10.644 --> 15:12.477
It's not.

15:12.479 --> 15:14.145
That lawyer had all the facts
all twisted, he's making

15:14.147 --> 15:15.980
this whole stink about it.

15:15.982 --> 15:17.515
That guy had himself a knife.

15:17.517 --> 15:19.050
Didn't he have a knife on him?
CAL:<i> Sheriff...</i>

15:19.052 --> 15:21.286
That is between you,
him and the fence post.

15:21.288 --> 15:23.254
I am here on more
prudent matters.

15:23.256 --> 15:25.023
He called me Sheriff again.

15:25.025 --> 15:26.557
Listen, son...

15:26.559 --> 15:28.159
If you're gonna stand on
my property with that belly

15:28.161 --> 15:29.661
growlin' for one of
my chickens, you'll call

15:29.663 --> 15:32.163
me dad, pa, father...

15:32.165 --> 15:35.099
Or if you're feeling
especially tender, daddy.

15:37.537 --> 15:39.203
CAL:<i> Done!</i>

15:39.205 --> 15:42.240
I'm here on matters other than
your fence post escapades.

15:42.242 --> 15:44.309
Escapades?

15:45.946 --> 15:47.211
He's back.

15:47.213 --> 15:53.418
<i> ¶ [SUSPENSE] ¶</i>

15:53.420 --> 16:01.492
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

16:02.329 --> 16:05.363
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

16:05.365 --> 16:07.432
CAL:<i> Now have you seen this?</i>

16:08.601 --> 16:11.536
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS OUTSIDE]</i>

16:11.538 --> 16:13.171
No.

16:13.173 --> 16:14.305
If I knew where he was,
I would've hunted and

16:14.307 --> 16:16.507
found him a long time ago.

16:16.509 --> 16:18.376
I know where he is.

16:18.378 --> 16:21.012
You<i> think</i> you do. I do.

16:21.014 --> 16:22.647
Even if you think you
do, he's not gettable.

16:22.649 --> 16:24.983
Not just the two of you.

16:24.985 --> 16:28.319
CAL:<i> Well, someone has to try.</i>

16:28.321 --> 16:31.322
I have a warrant for his arrest.

16:31.324 --> 16:33.458
That's just a piece of
rollin' paper to him.

16:33.460 --> 16:34.726
CAL:<i> It is my duty to deliver</i>

16:34.728 --> 16:36.661
that warrant and
to bring him back.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.463
JOHN: A warrant for The Saint?

16:38.465 --> 16:40.565
Well, whose boot did he spit
on, because jayhawkers like

16:40.567 --> 16:44.035
that are small potatoes
to the likes of Washington.

16:44.037 --> 16:45.570
There have been whispers...

16:45.572 --> 16:48.239
and rumors that have made it
all the way to Washington.

16:48.241 --> 16:50.475
Rumors rubbed together
don't make a warrant.

16:50.477 --> 16:53.544
CAL:<i> We have information</i>
that him and his crew...

16:53.546 --> 16:56.314
<i> they have been hitting</i>
reconstruction supply lines,

16:56.316 --> 16:59.617
<i> raiding encampments,</i>
profiteering, leaving a mess

16:59.619 --> 17:01.185
<i> wherever they hit!</i>

17:01.187 --> 17:04.389
Taking supplies,
women, leaving bodies!

17:04.391 --> 17:07.425
Now all that intel,
that leads here.

17:08.395 --> 17:10.028
Kansas?

17:10.030 --> 17:11.596
<i> [CHUCKLES]</i>

17:11.598 --> 17:13.531
You start flipping rocks
over in Kansas, you're

17:13.533 --> 17:16.768
gonna find more desperate
deserters than rattlesnakes.

17:16.770 --> 17:20.571
You're better off asking Grant
for a regiment of expendables.

17:22.675 --> 17:24.609
The president?

17:24.611 --> 17:26.244
The government asked<i> me.</i>

17:26.246 --> 17:29.447
And now, I'm asking you.

17:29.449 --> 17:31.549
Wha-

17:31.551 --> 17:33.518
What?

17:33.520 --> 17:36.788
Well, why didn't you say
that in the first place?

17:36.790 --> 17:38.689
I was trying to.

17:38.691 --> 17:41.459
The only thing is you would
need to become my deputy.

17:41.461 --> 17:43.828
<i> [LAUGHING]</i> A deputy, Break.

17:43.830 --> 17:45.630
A deputy?

17:45.632 --> 17:48.566
Well, we would have
to cross state lines.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.435
John...

17:50.437 --> 17:53.337
CAL:<i> The Saint has been stirring</i>
up all kinds of trouble.

17:53.339 --> 17:54.639
<i> Pickin' fights with</i>

17:54.641 --> 17:57.475
deserters, bushwhackers,
any southerner...

17:57.477 --> 17:59.644
<i> that's paths he cross.</i>

17:59.646 --> 18:05.349
The bounty is unwarranted
and unsanctioned but...

18:05.351 --> 18:11.355
<i> it is backed by rich</i>
investors and carpetbaggers.

18:11.357 --> 18:13.858
<i> Bounty hunters from all over</i>
have been winding up dead.

18:13.860 --> 18:17.662
<i> Everybody wants this reward</i>
but nobody can claim it.

18:22.235 --> 18:24.402
JOHN: Carpetbaggers,
banking bushwhackers.

18:24.404 --> 18:26.704
Trespassing bounty hunters.

18:26.706 --> 18:29.240
Bobby the bear.

18:29.242 --> 18:31.242
I told you somethin'
was cookin'.

18:31.244 --> 18:33.244
You warned me, 100.

18:33.246 --> 18:34.645
CAL:<i> This man wants war.</i>

18:34.647 --> 18:36.380
If he can light a fire, he will.

18:36.382 --> 18:38.683
Now if the bushwhackers
get him, then...

18:38.685 --> 18:42.820
But this man is living as
if the war is still on.

18:42.822 --> 18:47.391
If he keeps going on the
way that he is then...

18:47.393 --> 18:49.427
he could reignite the Civil War.

18:49.429 --> 18:57.435
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

18:57.437 --> 18:59.337
Now hold on.
The Saint's a slippery one.

18:59.339 --> 19:01.439
He's not gonna be stopped with
a smile and a piece of paper.

19:01.441 --> 19:02.240
CAL:<i> Then we bring him</i>

19:02.242 --> 19:03.808
inthe hard way.

19:03.810 --> 19:05.409
Cut from the same cloth.

19:05.411 --> 19:07.879
Like wool, in summer.

19:09.849 --> 19:12.183
Alright...

19:12.185 --> 19:13.618
Show me something about
his little group here.

19:13.620 --> 19:16.154
I'm not used to The Saint
having a gaggle with him.

19:16.156 --> 19:22.793
<i> [PAPERS RUSTLING]</i>

19:22.795 --> 19:24.729
This is Anvil.

19:24.731 --> 19:27.231
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

19:27.233 --> 19:29.200
<i> [BRASS CLINKS]</i>

19:29.202 --> 19:31.302
<i> [PANTING]</i>

19:31.304 --> 19:39.343
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

19:41.214 --> 19:43.447
<i> [GRUNTING]</i>

19:44.317 --> 19:47.852
<i> [FIGHTING]</i>

19:49.189 --> 19:50.855
<i> [PUNCHES]</i>

19:50.857 --> 19:52.557
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

19:52.559 --> 19:58.196
<i> [FIGHTING]</i>

19:59.832 --> 20:01.732
CAL: He can and will shoot
you dead in a heartbeat.

20:01.734 --> 20:04.769
<i> But he prefers to</i>
fight more personal.

20:04.771 --> 20:08.206
<i> They say his fists might</i>
as well be horse hooves.

20:08.208 --> 20:11.609
<i> Weapon of choice:</i>
Brass knuckles.

20:11.611 --> 20:13.477
I got it, don't get close.

20:13.479 --> 20:15.880
Easier said than done.

20:15.882 --> 20:17.882
<i> Meet Holt.</i>

20:17.884 --> 20:19.917
<i> [MEN FIGHTING IN BACKGROUND]</i>
[BULLET CLINKING]

20:19.919 --> 20:21.252
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

20:21.254 --> 20:27.458
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

20:27.460 --> 20:29.293
CAL:<i> A hunter.</i>

20:29.295 --> 20:31.963
<i> You'll hear his gunshot</i>
before you see him comin'.

20:33.633 --> 20:36.367
<i> Franklin York.</i>

20:36.369 --> 20:38.002
<i> [MEN SHOUTING]</i>

20:38.004 --> 20:39.437
SOLDIER:<i> We're being ambushed!</i>

20:39.439 --> 20:41.305
<i> Go, go, ride for help!</i>

20:41.307 --> 20:43.507
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

20:43.509 --> 20:45.509
CAL: One of the best
snipers in the business.

20:45.511 --> 20:47.979
<i> If he can see you in the</i>
distance, he can hit you.

20:47.981 --> 20:51.482
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

20:51.484 --> 20:52.817
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

20:52.819 --> 20:56.487
<i> ¶ [SUSPENSE] ¶</i>

20:56.489 --> 21:03.027
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

21:03.029 --> 21:05.596
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

21:05.598 --> 21:07.298
<i> [GRUNT]</i>

21:10.270 --> 21:12.303
CAL: Claims that he's shot
more than a dozen officers

21:12.305 --> 21:14.538
<i> off their horses.</i>

21:14.540 --> 21:17.441
<i> Says he doesn't miss.</i>

21:17.443 --> 21:19.610
JOHN:<i> Everybody misses.</i>

21:19.612 --> 21:21.045
<i> Who's next?</i>

21:21.047 --> 21:23.014
CAL:<i> George Washington, Jr.</i>

21:23.016 --> 21:24.015
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

21:24.017 --> 21:24.982
<i> [GRUNT]</i>

21:24.984 --> 21:26.751
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

21:26.753 --> 21:29.654
<i> Claims he's the direct</i>
descendant of the president.

21:29.656 --> 21:33.457
<i> Says if America was a</i>
monarchy he'd be king.

21:33.459 --> 21:37.061
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

21:37.063 --> 21:39.030
JOHN:<i> Washington didn't</i>
have any kids.

21:39.032 --> 21:40.364
CAL:<i> He didn't?</i>

21:40.366 --> 21:41.932
<i> Well, don't tell him that.</i>

21:41.934 --> 21:43.601
<i> Tucker Macready.</i>

21:43.603 --> 21:46.737
<i> He will kill anyone he</i>
sees as a rebel sympathizer.

21:46.739 --> 21:48.906
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

21:49.842 --> 21:51.075
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

21:51.077 --> 21:53.978
<i> [CLICK]</i>

21:53.980 --> 21:55.046
<i> [GRUNTS ANGRILY]</i>

21:55.048 --> 22:01.519
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

22:01.521 --> 22:03.354
<i> [COCKS GUN] [HITTING]</i>

22:03.356 --> 22:04.422
Aah!!

22:04.424 --> 22:05.956
<i> [SLAP, GUITAR STRINGS POP]</i>

22:05.958 --> 22:07.591
<i> They say he's the</i>
musician of the group and.

22:07.593 --> 22:09.427
<i> The Saint's right hand man.</i>

22:09.429 --> 22:11.696
<i> And he is mean.</i>

22:11.698 --> 22:14.098
<i> [MANIACAL LAUGH]</i>

22:16.035 --> 22:17.902
Music, the great equalizer.

22:17.904 --> 22:20.037
<i> [CHUCKLING]</i>

22:20.039 --> 22:22.340
CAL:<i> Stacey Snyder.</i>

22:22.342 --> 22:23.841
A girl.

22:23.843 --> 22:27.578
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

22:27.580 --> 22:30.915
<i> [GRUNTING]</i>

22:32.885 --> 22:36.721
CAL:<i> An unknown,</i>
a mystery, a liability.

22:36.723 --> 22:38.489
<i>Pretty, but you'll hit the floor</i>

22:38.491 --> 22:41.859
<i> before you can say, "Miss."</i>

22:41.861 --> 22:43.627
<i> They say she holds</i>
her own though, against

22:43.629 --> 22:45.596
<i> the rest of the bunch.</i>

22:45.598 --> 22:48.032
<i> Makes her scary enough for me.</i>

22:48.034 --> 22:51.902
I don't ever remember
having to fight no woman.

22:51.904 --> 22:55.473
That's because mom whooped
you a long time ago.

22:55.475 --> 22:57.908
JOHN:<i> Well, maybe I should show</i>
these people how I curbed

22:57.910 --> 23:00.111
your teens over my knee.

23:00.113 --> 23:03.147
I don't fight my subordinates,
Deputy Breaker.

23:03.149 --> 23:05.716
Deputy Breaker, Deputy...
<i> [CHUCKLING]</i>

23:05.718 --> 23:07.418
JOHN: What's in a title?

23:07.420 --> 23:10.755
Just a word made up by some
man sitting behind a desk.

23:10.757 --> 23:12.790
Besides...

23:12.792 --> 23:15.726
What better company
for my compromise?

23:15.728 --> 23:23.000
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

23:23.002 --> 23:26.737
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

23:26.739 --> 23:31.742
CAL:<i> And of course they</i>
are all led by Virgil.

23:31.744 --> 23:33.544
JOHN:<i> "The Saint."</i>

23:33.546 --> 23:40.050
<i> ¶</i> [OMINOUS] ¶

23:40.052 --> 23:48.092
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

23:48.094 --> 23:52.029
"We must extinguish
our resentments...

23:52.031 --> 23:54.965
if we want harmony and union."

23:54.967 --> 23:58.202
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

23:58.204 --> 24:00.671
Your newspaper's outdated.

24:00.673 --> 24:07.978
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

24:07.980 --> 24:09.947
Where's the gold?

24:11.217 --> 24:13.117
I don't know what
you're talking about.

24:13.119 --> 24:15.686
We were only transporting
food and supplies

24:15.688 --> 24:17.221
to the starving in St. Louis.

24:17.223 --> 24:25.496
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

24:26.866 --> 24:28.599
<i> [PUNCHING]</i>

24:28.601 --> 24:31.035
<i> [GASPING]</i>

24:31.037 --> 24:34.538
Kansas supplies
for Missouri rebels.

24:34.540 --> 24:36.106
OFFICER:<i> I swear.</i>

24:36.108 --> 24:37.975
There's no money!

24:37.977 --> 24:43.581
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

24:43.583 --> 24:44.982
<i> [YELLS]</i>

24:44.984 --> 24:46.717
I don't trust bushwhackers.

24:46.719 --> 24:48.752
I'm not a bushwhacker!

24:48.754 --> 24:53.090
I'm an officer of
the Union army.

24:53.092 --> 24:58.696
I serve Bates Guard, sixth
Missouri volunteer infantry!

24:58.698 --> 25:02.199
Bates Guard? Yes sir!

25:02.201 --> 25:05.202
I... I'm sorry, sir.

25:05.204 --> 25:06.737
Untie him.

25:06.739 --> 25:12.543
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

25:12.545 --> 25:13.844
Have a seat.

25:13.846 --> 25:15.880
Have a seat, c'mon.

25:20.286 --> 25:22.052
<i> [EXHALES]</i>

25:22.054 --> 25:30.127
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

25:30.897 --> 25:33.230
You have any children?

25:33.232 --> 25:35.099
I got three boys.

25:38.771 --> 25:41.138
I had two sons.

25:41.140 --> 25:44.875
They used to help me run
my spread, not too far

25:44.877 --> 25:46.644
from here actually.

25:46.646 --> 25:51.615
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

25:51.617 --> 25:54.151
One of them decided he
didn't like farming.

25:54.153 --> 25:57.054
Wanted to try his luck
on the Mississippi.

25:57.056 --> 26:00.257
I condemned it, naturally.

26:00.259 --> 26:08.699
But I woke to find he took my
best horse and my favorite gun

26:08.701 --> 26:13.704
and ran off, leaving me and
my other son to run the place.

26:13.706 --> 26:17.741
On the eve of the war,
he came back to me.

26:17.743 --> 26:21.812
Robbed, beaten, half starved.

26:21.814 --> 26:27.217
He came back to me with an
apologetic grin, a smirk.

26:27.219 --> 26:28.786
He said...

26:28.788 --> 26:31.689
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

26:31.691 --> 26:33.824
"I'm sorry, daddy.

26:33.826 --> 26:36.827
You were right."

26:36.829 --> 26:39.029
And I said, "I know."

26:40.866 --> 26:43.000
And shut the door in his face.

26:44.637 --> 26:48.272
George... OFFICER:<i> Wait!!</i>

26:48.274 --> 26:51.108
Wait!! We have to stomp
out the rebellion.

26:51.110 --> 26:52.242
OFFICER:<i> Please!!</i> Smite it.

26:52.244 --> 26:55.813
No!!! Shut the door on it.

26:55.815 --> 26:57.848
George, okay.

26:57.850 --> 26:58.916
Wait!!

26:58.918 --> 27:00.384
It's in the wagon!

27:04.991 --> 27:06.390
Under the seat.

27:09.095 --> 27:10.761
<i> [BREAKS LOCK]</i>

27:14.367 --> 27:17.034
TUCKER: Welcome to The Saint's
restoration of the Union

27:17.036 --> 27:19.303
and the final annihilation
of the Confederacy.

27:19.305 --> 27:22.139
THE SAINT:<i> Saddle up, boys!</i>

27:22.141 --> 27:23.674
<i> [SMOOCH]</i>

27:23.676 --> 27:26.010
George, the door.

27:28.314 --> 27:33.017
<i> ¶ Mine eyes have</i>
seen the glory... ¶

27:33.019 --> 27:34.918
<i> [COCKS GUN] [CHUCKLING]</i>

27:34.920 --> 27:36.820
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

27:39.792 --> 27:46.030
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

27:47.266 --> 27:48.265
<i> [SIGHS]</i>

27:48.267 --> 27:50.067
John...

27:51.404 --> 27:53.871
I finally get to fix my mistake.

27:56.409 --> 27:58.342
<i> This</i> is a mistake.

28:01.013 --> 28:03.414
My two against all of them?

28:03.416 --> 28:05.349
Well, four.

28:06.852 --> 28:09.019
There's four, actually.

28:11.257 --> 28:14.058
My boys... both of you?

28:16.328 --> 28:21.065
Well, trouble halved
is trouble shared.

28:21.067 --> 28:23.701
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS OUTSIDE]</i>

28:23.703 --> 28:26.003
Don't sally me, John.

28:26.005 --> 28:27.838
I'm not your deputy.

28:29.108 --> 28:30.908
Look me in the eye.

28:30.910 --> 28:34.978
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

28:34.980 --> 28:37.881
You've been dodging
bullets your whole life.

28:37.883 --> 28:41.051
And now I can't help but feel
you're stepping right into one.

28:45.324 --> 28:48.358
When you show a man mercy

28:48.360 --> 28:50.461
it becomes your responsibility.

28:52.865 --> 28:54.131
<i> [SIGHS]</i>

28:54.133 --> 28:56.934
Surely there's someone
else who can do this.

29:00.172 --> 29:01.839
No.

29:03.476 --> 29:05.109
I<i> have</i> to do this, Bonnie.

29:07.446 --> 29:09.913
No, you don't.

29:10.850 --> 29:14.218
You<i> want</i> to.

29:14.220 --> 29:17.387
And if you fail, that'll be why.

29:19.458 --> 29:21.225
Bonnie...

29:21.227 --> 29:29.299
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

29:29.301 --> 29:33.036
<i> [CRUMPLES UP PAPER]</i>

29:33.038 --> 29:38.842
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

29:38.844 --> 29:44.414
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

29:44.416 --> 29:48.118
<i> [GUNFIRE, MEN SHOUTING]</i>

29:48.120 --> 29:49.453
OFFICER:<i> Go back, retreat!</i>

29:49.455 --> 29:52.422
<i> Retreat, that's it boys,</i>
keep it moving!

29:52.424 --> 29:54.057
<i> We've got 'em on the run!</i>

29:55.327 --> 29:57.895
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

29:57.897 --> 30:00.464
<i> [GUNSHOT, GRUNT]</i>
OFFICER: I got one!

30:00.466 --> 30:02.933
<i> [GUNFIRE]</i>

30:02.935 --> 30:09.439
<i> [INDECIPHERABLE CHATTER]</i>

30:09.441 --> 30:17.514
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

30:20.519 --> 30:24.822
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

30:24.824 --> 30:26.490
<i> [GRUNTS]</i>

30:29.228 --> 30:30.894
That's enough for today, son.

30:32.398 --> 30:34.498
Cal...

30:34.500 --> 30:42.573
<i> [GUNFIRE]</i>

30:48.981 --> 30:50.514
VIRGIL:<i> Hold up, son.</i>

30:50.516 --> 30:52.482
Stand guard.

30:56.922 --> 30:58.522
<i> [SPITS]</i>

30:58.524 --> 31:06.163
<i> [GUNFIRE]</i>

31:06.165 --> 31:07.898
Jackpot.

31:07.900 --> 31:12.569
This gold watch will
fetch a pretty penny.

31:12.571 --> 31:14.238
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

31:14.240 --> 31:18.008
<i> ¶ [SUSPENSE] ¶</i>

31:18.010 --> 31:19.643
Maybe I'll even give
it to you, son.

31:19.645 --> 31:21.278
Come on, dad, stop.

31:21.280 --> 31:23.180
What?<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

31:23.182 --> 31:24.915
You've taken enough.

31:24.917 --> 31:26.516
No!!

31:28.053 --> 31:29.987
<i> [GUNSHOT] [BULLET RICOCHETS]</i>

31:32.024 --> 31:33.457
Perkins.

31:33.459 --> 31:37.094
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

31:37.096 --> 31:38.495
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

31:41.300 --> 31:42.966
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

31:42.968 --> 31:45.035
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

31:45.037 --> 31:46.904
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

31:46.906 --> 31:49.640
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

31:49.642 --> 31:57.581
<i> [GUNFIRE]</i>

31:57.583 --> 31:59.549
JOHN:<i> Cal, stand guard.</i>

31:59.551 --> 32:07.624
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

32:08.227 --> 32:15.299
<i> [PANTING]</i>

32:15.301 --> 32:18.335
Virgil, I'm so sorry.

32:18.337 --> 32:26.410
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

32:28.314 --> 32:30.347
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

32:30.349 --> 32:38.455
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

32:38.457 --> 32:40.724
I never should've brought him.

32:42.661 --> 32:44.995
JOHN:<i> He fought for</i>
a good cause, Virgil.

32:44.997 --> 32:47.331
With honor.

32:47.333 --> 32:50.567
VIRGIL: He fought
because I made him.

32:50.569 --> 32:54.271
He's dead because I brought him.

32:54.273 --> 32:56.173
It should've been his brother.

32:58.711 --> 33:00.744
But<i> he</i> was there.

33:00.746 --> 33:03.146
And that's what matters.

33:03.148 --> 33:04.982
The cause was affected
for the good because

33:04.984 --> 33:06.383
your son was part of it.

33:06.385 --> 33:08.685
And history will remember.

33:08.687 --> 33:12.089
VIRGIL: The cause... History...

33:14.660 --> 33:17.427
He came for the adventure.

33:19.365 --> 33:22.099
I came to kill traitors.

33:26.405 --> 33:29.139
I'll bring you home, boy.

33:29.141 --> 33:33.276
Lay you next to your
mother soon enough.

33:33.278 --> 33:38.248
As soon as I get that gray
back that murdered you.

33:38.250 --> 33:40.317
I'll kill him, boy.

33:40.319 --> 33:45.455
<i> [SNIFFS]</i>

33:45.457 --> 33:46.656
I'll...

33:46.658 --> 33:49.259
I'll have justice.

33:49.261 --> 33:51.161
JOHN:<i> Virgil...</i>

33:51.163 --> 33:54.264
that ain't justice.

33:54.266 --> 33:57.434
Red feather in his cap.

33:57.436 --> 34:01.238
Cocky, taunting red feather.

34:01.240 --> 34:03.640
I'll... find him.

34:03.642 --> 34:10.347
I'll find him if I have to
pillage the whole rebel army.

34:10.349 --> 34:13.650
Grieve him, Virgil,
fight for him.

34:13.652 --> 34:16.686
But don't dishonor
him with revenge.

34:16.688 --> 34:21.191
<i> [CROW CAWING]</i>

34:24.129 --> 34:26.296
Who up and made you preacher?

34:26.298 --> 34:28.799
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

34:28.801 --> 34:30.734
Look who you're talking to.

34:30.736 --> 34:32.536
Look where I'm standing!

34:32.538 --> 34:35.739
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

34:35.741 --> 34:37.841
Your boy knew what was right...

34:37.843 --> 34:40.077
he would've killed that Johnny.

34:40.079 --> 34:42.279
But you stopped him.

34:42.281 --> 34:47.317
My boy's dead because
<i> you</i> stopped that bullet.

34:47.319 --> 34:50.120
His blood cries for revenge!

34:50.122 --> 34:53.423
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

34:53.425 --> 34:55.192
Maybe it's yours that
should be taken.

34:55.194 --> 34:56.693
<i>[COCKS GUN]</i> JOHN: Hold it, Buge.

34:59.565 --> 35:01.164
Virgil...

35:01.767 --> 35:04.234
CAL:<i> Dad...</i>

35:04.236 --> 35:05.602
JOHN:<i> It's alright, Cal.</i>

35:05.604 --> 35:10.507
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

35:10.509 --> 35:12.642
<i> [LOWERS HAMMER]</i>

35:14.446 --> 35:17.147
<i> [SOBBING]</i> I'm sorry boy.

35:17.149 --> 35:25.355
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

35:25.357 --> 35:28.425
Take it.

35:28.427 --> 35:30.627
He'd want you to...

35:30.629 --> 35:32.295
keep practicing.

35:38.904 --> 35:47.177
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA PLAYING] ¶</i>

35:50.349 --> 35:58.421
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA CONTINUES] ¶</i>

36:00.425 --> 36:06.763
<i> ¶ [HARMONICA CONTINUES] ¶</i>

36:08.167 --> 36:10.834
You're pretty good at
that tin sandwich.

36:10.836 --> 36:12.469
<i> [BLOWS]</i>

36:13.939 --> 36:16.406
You think if Perkins was
still alive The Saint

36:16.408 --> 36:18.208
would've turned out the same?

36:18.210 --> 36:21.845
I think The Saint was broke
before the war even started.

36:21.847 --> 36:24.848
There was bad brewing
in him for a long time.

36:24.850 --> 36:28.385
I think when his son
died, that dam broke.

36:30.856 --> 36:33.957
No, I don't think
The Saint's son was bad.

36:33.959 --> 36:37.861
But I think the father would've
forced him there eventually.

36:37.863 --> 36:41.965
You see, daddies have a way
of doing those things.

36:41.967 --> 36:44.768
Shaping a thing.

36:44.770 --> 36:46.903
So you shaped me, huh?

36:46.905 --> 36:48.905
JOHN:<i> Well, not to the</i>
caliber that you've become.

36:48.907 --> 36:52.342
But I think mama and me,
we lit some kindling.

36:52.344 --> 36:57.280
But you stoked that fire
all by yourself,<i> senator.</i>

36:57.282 --> 36:58.815
Oh, I know. Come on...

36:58.817 --> 37:02.953
Oh, well, war hero.

37:02.955 --> 37:05.922
Law school, marshal.

37:05.924 --> 37:09.626
Going after the number one
criminal this side of the Ohio.

37:09.628 --> 37:12.295
Dad. You haven't shown
any interest in.

37:12.297 --> 37:14.965
The Saint till it caught
the eye of Washington.

37:14.967 --> 37:17.400
I ain't condemning you,
I get it.

37:17.402 --> 37:18.969
Small potatoes.

37:18.971 --> 37:22.305
But let this be a lesson to you.

37:22.307 --> 37:26.543
Small things, grow.

37:26.545 --> 37:28.445
Let's just worry about
getting The Saint.

37:28.447 --> 37:31.982
We'll think about
the becomings, after.

37:31.984 --> 37:33.617
I can't help but wonder
what it would've been like

37:33.619 --> 37:35.518
if I hadn't let him go.

37:35.520 --> 37:37.254
Well, he was your friend.

37:37.256 --> 37:39.389
No, he wasn't.

37:39.391 --> 37:43.293
Just because you know a man
doesn't make him your friend.

37:49.901 --> 37:52.302
What was the story
with that fence post?

37:52.304 --> 37:57.040
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

37:57.042 --> 37:58.708
Good night, Cal.

37:58.710 --> 38:00.910
Good night! Good night.

38:00.912 --> 38:08.985
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

38:10.922 --> 38:15.525
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

38:15.527 --> 38:23.600
<i> ¶ ["THE WARRANT" THEME] ¶</i>

38:24.069 --> 38:28.872
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

38:28.874 --> 38:36.946
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

38:38.350 --> 38:40.884
I<i> will</i> be back.

38:40.886 --> 38:42.619
Both of you.

38:45.090 --> 38:46.756
Hyah, hyah!

38:47.693 --> 38:55.765
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

38:56.935 --> 39:05.008
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

39:06.912 --> 39:14.551
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

39:14.553 --> 39:19.556
<i> [WATER SPLASHING]</i>

39:19.558 --> 39:23.526
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

39:23.528 --> 39:25.495
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

39:25.497 --> 39:32.535
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

39:32.537 --> 39:35.372
<i> [CHICKENS CLUCK]</i>

39:35.374 --> 39:43.446
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

39:44.683 --> 39:52.722
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

39:53.825 --> 40:01.898
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

40:02.801 --> 40:10.874
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

40:10.876 --> 40:16.579
BLACKJACK: The Saint stole
our food, stole our lives.

40:16.581 --> 40:20.417
<i> And this reward will</i>
give it all back!

40:20.419 --> 40:24.554
<i> I want you to think of your</i>
wives; Think about your sister.

40:24.556 --> 40:26.022
Think about your children.

40:26.024 --> 40:30.193
This time tomorrow,
our problems are over!

40:30.195 --> 40:33.430
This time tomorrow there'll be
justice for our fallen brothers.

40:33.432 --> 40:34.631
That's right!

40:34.633 --> 40:36.733
This time tomorrow
we'll be rich!

40:38.870 --> 40:41.104
Kill him, hang him dead.

40:41.106 --> 40:43.740
Somebody gets between
you and The Saint...

40:43.742 --> 40:46.176
They're standin' between
you and your family,

40:46.178 --> 40:49.145
you and your lives!

40:49.147 --> 40:51.481
Let's fight for the fallen!

40:51.483 --> 40:52.816
Let's ride!

40:52.818 --> 40:54.150
RUCKUS:<i> Let's make some money.</i>

40:54.152 --> 40:55.518
CLETUS:<i> Alright, let's get him.</i>

40:55.520 --> 40:56.553
BLACKJACK:<i> Saddle up boys!</i>

40:56.555 --> 40:57.787
RUCKUS:<i> Yeah, let's go!</i>

40:57.789 --> 41:05.495
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

41:05.497 --> 41:09.599
<i> [FIRE CRACKLING]</i>

41:10.802 --> 41:13.002
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

41:13.004 --> 41:15.071
What you readin'?

41:15.073 --> 41:17.674
Nothin'.

41:17.676 --> 41:19.142
JOHN:<i> Uh-huh.</i>

41:20.779 --> 41:23.146
CAL:<i> Sonnets.</i> Who?

41:23.148 --> 41:25.882
Shakespeare.

41:25.884 --> 41:28.818
Shakespeare?

41:28.820 --> 41:30.653
Poetry.

41:32.190 --> 41:36.226
Oh... Huh.

41:36.228 --> 41:38.528
JOHN:<i> You know...</i>

41:38.530 --> 41:40.029
I wrote a poem once.

41:43.235 --> 41:45.201
What, you? JOHN:<i> Uh-huh.</i>

41:45.203 --> 41:47.136
When I first met your mama.

41:47.138 --> 41:50.106
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

41:50.108 --> 41:54.177
Wow, I am surprised
I was even born.

41:54.179 --> 41:57.747
Yeah, I can be artistic
too when I want to be.

41:57.749 --> 41:59.916
Yeah.

41:59.918 --> 42:01.818
With a fence post.

42:01.820 --> 42:03.920
You're lucky I'm layin' down!

42:03.922 --> 42:05.989
Yeah, yeah.

42:05.991 --> 42:07.724
My watch.

42:07.726 --> 42:09.692
<i> Sleep tight, boys. Night.</i>

42:09.694 --> 42:17.767
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

42:19.304 --> 42:20.904
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

42:20.906 --> 42:22.705
Mama know?

42:22.707 --> 42:23.840
What, about the sonnets?

42:23.842 --> 42:25.775
About the<i> girl.</i>

42:25.777 --> 42:28.011
I would feel like picking with
the barrage of questions

42:28.013 --> 42:30.046
she would come at me with.

42:30.048 --> 42:32.215
No, I have not told anybody.

42:32.217 --> 42:35.852
You know, new canteens
are cheap.

42:35.854 --> 42:39.155
So is life.

42:39.157 --> 42:41.858
Yours was almost bought
with a tiny piece of lead.

42:43.662 --> 42:45.295
Old things like this always
remind me to pray

42:45.297 --> 42:47.196
for the better angels.

42:47.198 --> 42:50.166
<i> [FOOTSTEPS, HORSE NEIGHING]</i>

42:50.168 --> 42:51.768
Get some sleep.

42:51.770 --> 42:54.871
Nothing gets past ol' Buge.

42:54.873 --> 42:57.106
CAL: I don't think I've ever
seen him sleep a wink.

42:57.108 --> 43:00.577
I bet he would stay out there
all night if you asked him to.

43:00.579 --> 43:02.946
<i> [DEPUTY SHANKS SIGHS]</i>

43:02.948 --> 43:04.981
Looks all quiet to me.

43:07.986 --> 43:11.220
Shanks, how long have you
been marshaling for?

43:11.222 --> 43:14.090
Since the war.

43:14.092 --> 43:16.159
What made you choose<i> this</i>
line of work?

43:16.161 --> 43:17.694
DEPUTY SHANKS: Best legal way to
keep the juices flowing,

43:17.696 --> 43:19.295
I suppose.

43:19.297 --> 43:21.064
It's kinda hard to go back to
being a clerk

43:21.066 --> 43:23.833
once you've dealt in bullets,
know what I mean?

43:29.240 --> 43:31.374
Yeah.

43:31.376 --> 43:33.376
I suppose I do.

43:33.378 --> 43:35.778
DEPUTY SHANKS: My dad did.

43:35.780 --> 43:38.181
He went right back behind the
counter selling

43:38.183 --> 43:41.351
pickled eggs and candy sticks.

43:41.353 --> 43:43.353
I couldn't though.

43:46.725 --> 43:50.860
You know there are two types of
men who come in and out of war.

43:50.862 --> 43:55.898
Those who fight because
it's their duty like your daddy.

43:55.900 --> 44:00.937
Then go home and shed the
memories with their uniform.

44:00.939 --> 44:04.741
<i> And then there are those who</i>
fight because they're fighters,

44:04.743 --> 44:07.276
and there's always something
that needs to be fought.

44:09.948 --> 44:11.814
It takes both types.

44:11.816 --> 44:17.053
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

44:17.055 --> 44:18.888
Good night boys.

44:20.959 --> 44:22.825
<i> [SIGHS]</i>

44:22.827 --> 44:30.900
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

44:34.806 --> 44:43.146
<i> [BIRDS CHIRPING]</i>

44:43.148 --> 44:46.749
Hyah! Hyah!

44:46.751 --> 44:53.222
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

44:53.224 --> 44:55.124
<i> [HORSE NEIGHING]</i>

44:55.126 --> 45:02.432
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

45:02.434 --> 45:05.268
JOHN: We're getting pretty deep
into Kansas now boys.

45:05.270 --> 45:07.870
Are you sure you know
where The Saint is?

45:07.872 --> 45:10.039
Just relax back there, old man.

45:14.145 --> 45:15.745
The trail leads<i> that</i> way.

45:15.747 --> 45:17.880
But that's towards the
Abington place.

45:17.882 --> 45:19.382
Why would they go through
the Abington place?

45:19.384 --> 45:20.950
Something ain't right.

45:20.952 --> 45:22.318
I'm gonna go check it out.

45:22.320 --> 45:23.953
- Cal!
- Hyah!

45:23.955 --> 45:25.321
<i> [GRUMBLES]</i>

45:25.323 --> 45:28.124
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

45:28.126 --> 45:30.293
JOHN: Ah... stubborn.

45:30.295 --> 45:33.396
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

45:33.398 --> 45:35.064
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

45:35.066 --> 45:36.933
Something wrong, Sheriff?

45:36.935 --> 45:40.503
<i> [SIGHS]</i>

45:40.505 --> 45:42.271
Your daddy used to
get these feelings

45:42.273 --> 45:47.276
before a battle or a march,
you know about those?

45:47.278 --> 45:50.179
Yeah, I get 'em at
home too when something's off,

45:50.181 --> 45:53.382
or about to happen.

45:53.384 --> 45:55.184
How are you feeling?

45:59.390 --> 46:01.257
Like we're being watched.

46:01.259 --> 46:03.292
Uh-huh... yeah.

46:05.964 --> 46:08.865
I missed your daddy the last
couple of years.

46:08.867 --> 46:10.800
Yeah, I miss him too.

46:13.338 --> 46:15.805
He talked about you all
the time during the war.

46:15.807 --> 46:17.940
<i> ¶ [SOFT NOSTALGIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

46:17.942 --> 46:19.509
It was hard for him
fighting against ya.

46:19.511 --> 46:22.879
<i> ¶ [SOFT NOSTALGIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

46:22.881 --> 46:25.882
Every prisoner we'd catch, he'd
always ask them if they knew ya.

46:25.884 --> 46:29.218
<i> ¶ [SOFT NOSTALGIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

46:29.220 --> 46:31.354
<i> [PATS BACK]</i>
It's an honor ridin' with ya.

46:31.356 --> 46:32.789
I hope I don't
disappoint you, sir.

46:32.791 --> 46:34.524
Nah, you won't.

46:34.526 --> 46:35.792
<i> [APPROACHING HOOF BEATS]</i>

46:35.794 --> 46:37.193
<i> [HORSE NEIGHING]</i>

46:37.195 --> 46:38.795
They're there.

46:38.797 --> 46:40.296
And the Abingtons?

46:40.298 --> 46:42.565
Fresh graves in the back.

46:42.567 --> 46:44.300
CAL: There's a girl.<i> JOHN: Abby?</i>

46:44.302 --> 46:46.469
She was running water from the
well... she's alive.

46:46.471 --> 46:50.139
<i> ¶ [SOMBER MUSIC] ¶</i>

46:50.141 --> 46:52.341
<i> [FLASHBACK]</i>
THE SAINT: So, this is it.

46:52.343 --> 46:55.344
You hang a man for
avenging his son?

46:55.346 --> 46:58.548
DEPUTY SHANKS:
What's the plan, Marshal?

46:58.550 --> 47:00.483
CAL: Ride around the tree line
and come around back,

47:00.485 --> 47:02.251
and you cut their horses loose.

47:02.253 --> 47:05.321
If you see them run out,
give them light.

47:05.323 --> 47:07.356
Bugle, stay just out of
the line of fire.

47:07.358 --> 47:09.358
If there's trouble,
run and get help.

47:11.162 --> 47:12.962
Sheriff.

47:12.964 --> 47:13.996
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

47:13.998 --> 47:17.099
Or we deliver the warrant.

47:17.101 --> 47:21.137
Hup! Hyah!<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

47:21.139 --> 47:25.875
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

47:25.877 --> 47:31.180
<i> ¶ [TUNING, STRUMMING GUITAR] ¶</i>

47:31.182 --> 47:38.888
<i> [HOOF BEATS APPROACHING]</i>

47:38.890 --> 47:40.556
Company.

47:40.558 --> 47:44.627
<i> CAL: My name is Cal Breaker,</i>
and I am a U.S. Marshal.

47:44.629 --> 47:46.429
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

47:46.431 --> 47:48.231
Howdy.

47:48.233 --> 47:50.466
<i> CAL: Is Mr. Abington here?</i>

47:50.468 --> 47:53.336
TUCKER: Yeah, he's around.

47:53.338 --> 47:54.871
One of the...

47:54.873 --> 47:56.372
<i> twins</i> could take you to him.

47:56.374 --> 47:59.175
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i> Heh.

47:59.177 --> 48:02.211
<i> JOHN: Easy, Cal.</i>

48:02.213 --> 48:04.080
<i> [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]</i>

48:04.082 --> 48:05.915
You ever grab a
rattler by the nose?

48:05.917 --> 48:08.184
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

48:08.186 --> 48:11.954
Grab those reins,
and you'll find out.

48:11.956 --> 48:13.923
<i> That's right.</i>

48:13.925 --> 48:17.193
TUCKER: You're in no position to
make threats, law dog.

48:17.195 --> 48:19.262
Virgil!

48:19.264 --> 48:21.664
Virgil, come on out!

48:21.666 --> 48:25.601
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

48:25.603 --> 48:31.908
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

48:31.910 --> 48:33.209
John Breaker.

48:33.211 --> 48:35.611
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

48:35.613 --> 48:37.280
Virg.

48:37.282 --> 48:39.916
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

48:39.918 --> 48:42.919
It always makes me smile
to see you, John.

48:42.921 --> 48:45.187
I wish I felt the same, Virg.

48:45.189 --> 48:46.622
VIRGIL: The last time I saw you,

48:46.624 --> 48:48.691
you were fitting me for a noose.

48:48.693 --> 48:50.526
If memory serves,
you deserved it.

48:50.528 --> 48:55.164
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

48:55.166 --> 48:57.233
Are you here to see the uh...

48:57.235 --> 48:58.634
<i> JOHN: Abingtons.</i>

48:58.636 --> 49:00.303
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

49:00.305 --> 49:04.373
Yeah, are you here to see them?
Because they ain't here.

49:04.375 --> 49:06.075
Hmm.

49:06.077 --> 49:09.645
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

49:09.647 --> 49:13.015
Looks like you made
yourself at home.

49:13.017 --> 49:14.951
I know you ain't here on
official business,

49:14.953 --> 49:17.620
because last time I checked,
the state line ended over yonder

49:17.622 --> 49:20.056
and so does your jurisdiction.

49:20.058 --> 49:21.524
Mine did...

49:21.526 --> 49:23.259
<i> his</i> didn't.

49:23.261 --> 49:25.628
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

49:25.630 --> 49:27.263
Cal?

49:27.265 --> 49:29.031
Virgil.

49:29.033 --> 49:30.099
Well...

49:30.101 --> 49:31.534
this boy he...

49:31.536 --> 49:34.203
he was friends with
my boy during the war.

49:34.205 --> 49:35.604
It's good to see you, Cal.

49:35.606 --> 49:36.973
It's "Marshal" now.

49:36.975 --> 49:39.108
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

49:39.110 --> 49:40.476
Marshal?

49:40.478 --> 49:43.079
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

49:43.081 --> 49:47.483
Good for you, good for you, heh.

49:47.485 --> 49:49.452
<i>What can I do for you, Marshal?</i>

49:49.454 --> 49:51.520
We have got a warrant
for your arrest.

49:51.522 --> 49:54.423
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

49:54.425 --> 49:56.225
Yeah?

49:56.227 --> 49:59.261
I don't think so, Cal.

49:59.263 --> 50:02.164
It's nice of you
boys to stop by.

50:02.166 --> 50:03.733
Goodbye, John.

50:03.735 --> 50:07.303
We ain't goin' without ya, Virg.

50:07.305 --> 50:10.506
Trouble's coming and it's
got your name all over it.

50:10.508 --> 50:14.010
Wouldn't you rather see this
through with some friends?

50:14.012 --> 50:15.578
Are we still friends, John?

50:15.580 --> 50:19.348
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

50:19.350 --> 50:21.384
We can do this easy, Virg.

50:21.386 --> 50:22.752
Ain't nothin' easy.

50:22.754 --> 50:25.254
<i> [BUGLE'S HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

50:27.525 --> 50:29.425
Bugle still fighting
your wars for you?

50:29.427 --> 50:31.360
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

50:31.362 --> 50:32.428
Holt!

50:32.430 --> 50:37.166
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

50:37.168 --> 50:40.202
She makes a<i> mean</i> cobbler.

50:40.204 --> 50:44.473
<i> [TUCKER LAUGHING]</i>

50:44.475 --> 50:46.442
Are you okay, Abby?

50:46.444 --> 50:48.244
<i> [BIRDS CHIRPING]</i>

50:48.246 --> 50:51.047
<i> [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]</i>

50:51.049 --> 50:55.151
VIRGIL: What are the odds
of you knowing them?

50:55.153 --> 50:57.620
JOHN: They used to live just
north of Linn Creek.

50:57.622 --> 50:59.688
VIRGIL:<i> Well, then...</i>
DEPUTY SHANKS: Get, get, get!

50:59.690 --> 51:02.224
VIRGIL: I guess you already
know all about the cobbler.

51:02.226 --> 51:03.726
<i> [VIRGIL'S GANG LAUGHS]</i>

51:03.728 --> 51:06.495
Now as much as I like
cobbler, Virg...

51:06.497 --> 51:08.731
you know how Bonnie gets
if I ruin her dinner.

51:08.733 --> 51:10.466
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

51:10.468 --> 51:13.502
Pace you're marchin, ya gonna
miss more than supper.

51:13.504 --> 51:16.338
It's more than you'll get hangin
from a bushwhacker's tree.

51:16.340 --> 51:19.341
Their trees or your gallows,
it makes no difference to me.
Listen, Virg-

51:19.343 --> 51:21.410
No<i> you</i> listen, John!
[COCKS PISTOL]

51:21.412 --> 51:24.180
<i> You take your Marshal-boy,</i>
and you go across that line.

51:24.182 --> 51:25.781
And you forget you ever knew me!

51:25.783 --> 51:28.417
Not his call, it's mine.

51:28.419 --> 51:30.319
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

51:30.321 --> 51:32.288
Back a bear in his own den,
boy...

51:32.290 --> 51:34.090
you'll find out what happens.

51:34.092 --> 51:37.626
JOHN: I know what happens...
you smoke him out.

51:37.628 --> 51:41.363
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

51:41.365 --> 51:43.766
VIRGIL:<i> We were brothers once.</i>

51:43.768 --> 51:45.868
<i> I'm gonna give you</i>
one last chance.

51:45.870 --> 51:47.837
<i> Take your boy home.</i>

51:47.839 --> 51:50.673
Don't make the same
mistake I did.

51:50.675 --> 51:51.807
Holt!<i> [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]</i>

51:51.809 --> 51:54.143
Tucker!<i> [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]</i>

51:54.145 --> 51:54.777
CAL: Hey. JOHN:<i> Cal.</i>

51:54.779 --> 51:56.479
Hey! Hey!

51:56.481 --> 51:58.881
- Cal, don't.
- Hey!<i> [DOOR SLAMS SHUT]</i>

51:58.883 --> 52:07.156
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

52:07.725 --> 52:09.859
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

52:09.861 --> 52:13.529
<i> [COCKS RIFLE, HORSE BLUSTERS]</i>

52:13.531 --> 52:15.564
Everybody stop.

52:15.566 --> 52:17.199
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

52:17.201 --> 52:17.900
Aw, heck.

52:17.902 --> 52:26.142
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

52:26.878 --> 52:28.410
Hyah!

52:28.412 --> 52:32.281
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

52:32.283 --> 52:35.618
<i> [COCKS RIFLE, GUNSHOTS]</i>

52:35.620 --> 52:38.220
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS, COCKS RIFLE]</i>

52:38.222 --> 52:42.224
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

52:42.226 --> 52:43.559
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

52:43.561 --> 52:44.693
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

52:44.695 --> 52:45.761
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

52:45.763 --> 52:49.632
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

52:49.634 --> 52:51.300
<i> [EXHALES]</i>

52:51.302 --> 52:54.270
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

52:54.272 --> 53:02.611
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

53:02.613 --> 53:04.446
<i> [COCKS RIFLE, FIRES GUNSHOT]</i>

53:04.448 --> 53:06.215
<i> [RICOCHETS, FIRES GUNSHOT]</i>

53:06.217 --> 53:10.319
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

53:10.321 --> 53:11.954
<i> [COCKS PISTOL]</i>

53:11.956 --> 53:13.756
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

53:13.758 --> 53:16.559
<i> [EXHALES]</i>

53:16.561 --> 53:20.496
<i> [GRUNTING, GROANING]</i>

53:20.498 --> 53:24.233
<i> [PUNCHING]</i>

53:24.235 --> 53:26.936
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

53:26.938 --> 53:28.504
<i> [GRUNTS, GROANS]</i>

53:28.506 --> 53:29.972
Yah!
<i> [FENCE BREAKING, CLATTERING]</i>

53:29.974 --> 53:33.943
<i> [JOHN GROANING]</i>

53:33.945 --> 53:38.547
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

53:38.549 --> 53:42.284
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

53:42.286 --> 53:46.789
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

53:46.791 --> 53:49.325
<i> [GUNSHOTS, HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

53:49.327 --> 53:51.227
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

53:51.229 --> 53:52.361
<i> [COCKS RIFLE HAMMER]</i>

53:52.363 --> 53:54.263
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

53:54.265 --> 53:59.768
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

53:59.770 --> 54:01.670
<i> [GUNSHOT, BUGLE GROANS]</i>

54:01.672 --> 54:04.907
<i>[HORSE CONTINUES TROTTING AWAY]</i>

54:04.909 --> 54:06.542
<i> [COCKS PISTOL]</i>

54:06.544 --> 54:09.311
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

54:09.313 --> 54:10.980
<i> [THUD]</i>

54:10.982 --> 54:14.516
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

54:14.518 --> 54:16.252
<i> [BRASS KNUCKLES CLINKING]</i>

54:16.254 --> 54:18.520
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

54:18.522 --> 54:20.356
Fence post!<i> [ANVIL GROANING]</i>

54:20.358 --> 54:22.891
Yah!<i> [GRUNTING]</i>

54:22.893 --> 54:24.260
<i> [ANVIL GROANING]</i>

54:24.262 --> 54:29.732
<i> [JOHN HITTING, ANVIL GROANING]</i>

54:29.734 --> 54:32.901
<i> [LOUD CLATTERING, SPLASHING]</i>

54:32.903 --> 54:34.903
Gentle justice.

54:34.905 --> 54:43.312
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

54:43.314 --> 54:44.580
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

54:44.582 --> 54:47.716
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

54:47.718 --> 54:55.791
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

54:56.627 --> 54:57.926
They got Bugle!

54:57.928 --> 55:00.429
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

55:00.431 --> 55:02.031
Did he hit the ground?

55:02.033 --> 55:05.634
<i> - What?</i>
- Did he fall from his horse?

55:05.636 --> 55:07.503
CAL:<i> No.</i>

55:07.505 --> 55:11.073
<i> [SIGHING]</i>

55:11.075 --> 55:12.474
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

55:12.476 --> 55:13.375
<i> [TUCKER FIRES GUNSHOT]</i>

55:13.377 --> 55:15.077
Ah!

55:15.079 --> 55:23.352
<i> ¶ [SOMBER MUSIC] ¶</i>

55:25.323 --> 55:30.793
<i> ¶ [SOMBER MUSIC] ¶</i>

55:30.795 --> 55:31.994
<i> [TUCKER LAUGHING]</i>

55:31.996 --> 55:34.963
<i> [STUMBLES TO GROUND]</i>

55:34.965 --> 55:43.038
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

55:46.344 --> 55:48.344
<i> [EMPTY CLICKING]</i>

55:48.346 --> 55:50.846
Cal!!!

55:50.848 --> 55:52.948
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>

55:52.950 --> 55:55.718
Cal, go! Go!

55:55.720 --> 56:00.422
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

56:00.424 --> 56:01.490
Go, Cal! Go!

56:01.492 --> 56:04.693
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

56:04.695 --> 56:06.795
Go, go! Get in! You ain't gonna
bring 'em back

56:06.797 --> 56:08.063
doing stuff like that!

56:08.065 --> 56:10.099
CAL:<i> They got Shanks.</i>

56:10.101 --> 56:11.433
JOHN: Ain't nothin' you can
do about that right now.

56:11.435 --> 56:12.568
CAL:<i> They killed him.</i>

56:12.570 --> 56:13.836
JOHN: We all knew the risks.

56:13.838 --> 56:16.939
CAL:
What kind of excuse is that?

56:16.941 --> 56:19.074
Cal!<i> [GUNSHOT WHIZZES BY]</i>

56:19.076 --> 56:20.676
He died fighting for a cause.

56:20.678 --> 56:22.144
That's all any fighter
can ever ask for.

56:22.146 --> 56:23.912
You going back out there and
getting yourself killed

56:23.914 --> 56:25.714
ain't gonna help him now.
<i> [GUNSHOT WHIZZES BY]</i>

56:25.716 --> 56:28.617
How about Bugle?
He was your friend.

56:28.619 --> 56:31.453
You said he didn't fall off
his horse, right?

56:31.455 --> 56:32.621
CAL:<i> Yeah.</i>

56:32.623 --> 56:34.490
I know my friend.

56:34.492 --> 56:36.859
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

56:36.861 --> 56:38.761
<i> [GUNSHOT WHIZZES BY]</i>

56:38.763 --> 56:41.964
CAL: You should have killed
Virgil when you had the chance.

56:41.966 --> 56:44.400
<i> [FLASHBACK] JOHN: Well let me</i>
<i> tell</i>
ya what redemption looks like...

56:44.402 --> 56:46.735
<i> I never found you,</i>
and I never see you again.

56:46.737 --> 56:49.838
You go West and start yourself
a new life, Virgil.

56:49.840 --> 56:51.407
You ready to move?

56:51.409 --> 56:54.810
<i> [EXHALES]</i>

56:54.812 --> 56:57.479
We gotta hold up until
we get reinforcements.

56:57.481 --> 56:59.515
CAL: How long is that gonna be?

56:59.517 --> 57:01.950
Well, it'll take Bugle 2 hours
to get to town;

57:01.952 --> 57:05.421
2 hours to posse up and about 5
hours to get back in the dark.

57:05.423 --> 57:06.822
So until dawn?

57:06.824 --> 57:09.124
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>
I ain't waitin' that long.

57:11.095 --> 57:18.133
<i> [GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE]</i>

57:18.135 --> 57:22.504
BUGLE:<i> Hey Breaker... Breaker.</i>
JOHN: Yeah?

57:22.506 --> 57:23.939
We've got trouble.

57:23.941 --> 57:25.507
<i> [GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE]</i>

57:25.509 --> 57:27.709
<i> [SIGHS]</i> Yeah.

57:29.146 --> 57:32.714
BUGLE: He left last night
right past the pickets.

57:34.985 --> 57:37.886
<i>They're calling him a deserter.</i>

57:37.888 --> 57:39.988
JOHN: We both know what
he went to do.

57:39.990 --> 57:41.857
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

57:41.859 --> 57:44.927
BUGLE: The Captain's
looking for him.

57:44.929 --> 57:46.762
They'll want me to
bring him back.

57:46.764 --> 57:49.164
<i> [BIRDS CHIRPING]</i>

57:49.166 --> 57:51.099
He who walks with the wise
becomes wise,

57:51.101 --> 57:52.768
but a companion to fools
suffers harm.

57:52.770 --> 57:56.839
<i> [CAL'S FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]</i>

57:56.841 --> 57:59.842
They're gonna hang him,
aren't they, dad?

57:59.844 --> 58:03.479
I know why me, but why<i> you?</i>

58:07.151 --> 58:08.750
Foolish or wise...

58:11.222 --> 58:13.255
I'm your companion.

58:14.925 --> 58:16.558
Here's to harm.

58:16.560 --> 58:18.160
<i> [MUGS CLINKING]</i>

58:18.162 --> 58:20.662
I'm comin' with ya.

58:20.664 --> 58:21.230
<i> [MUG CLINKS DOWN ON TABLE]</i>

58:21.232 --> 58:22.731
Not this time.

58:22.733 --> 58:23.932
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

58:23.934 --> 58:25.067
Dad?

58:25.069 --> 58:27.836
You're staying. It's safer here.

58:27.838 --> 58:30.639
CAL: But it's not safe anywhere,
and I wanna be with you.

58:30.641 --> 58:32.741
I said you're staying.

58:32.743 --> 58:34.877
If you die for your country,
so be it.

58:34.879 --> 58:37.079
But I'm not letting you die
for The Saint.

58:38.682 --> 58:39.882
Let's go.

58:39.884 --> 58:46.722
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

58:46.724 --> 58:49.691
<i> ¶ [CAL PLAYS HARMONICA] ¶</i>

58:49.693 --> 58:51.593
JOHN:<i> They got us pinned, Cal.</i>

58:51.595 --> 58:53.862
<i> Looks like we're staying</i>
here tonight.

58:53.864 --> 58:55.898
<i> ¶ ["BATTLE HYMN OF THE</i>
REPUBLIC," HARMONICA] ¶

58:55.900 --> 58:58.901
Heya... do you think
they'll run?

58:58.903 --> 59:00.569
No.

59:00.571 --> 59:02.538
CAL:<i> Do you think they'll</i>
hurt the girl?

59:02.540 --> 59:05.073
<i> [CRICKETS CHIRPING]</i>

59:05.075 --> 59:06.909
I don't know.

59:06.911 --> 59:11.146
<i> ¶ ["BATTLE HYMN OF THE</i>
REPUBLIC," HARMONICA] ¶

59:11.148 --> 59:13.148
<i> [BIRD SQUAWKS]</i>

59:13.150 --> 59:14.583
Shh.

59:14.585 --> 59:16.118
<i> [BIRD SQUAWKS OUTSIDE]</i>

59:16.120 --> 59:17.319
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

59:17.321 --> 59:20.222
<i> [FOOTSTEPS OUTSIDE]</i>

59:20.224 --> 59:21.924
<i> [SHOVEL CLANKING]</i>

59:21.926 --> 59:24.326
CAL: What are you doing?
JOHN: Shh.

59:24.328 --> 59:28.230
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

59:28.232 --> 59:31.266
JOHN: Hey!<i> [THUD]</i>

59:31.268 --> 59:33.068
<i> [MAN GROANING]</i>

59:33.070 --> 59:35.637
<i> [SHOVEL FALLS TO GROUND]</i>
I hit him, you cuff him.

59:39.944 --> 59:43.078
BLACKJACK: This is that
jayhawker Jeremiah's outpost.

59:43.080 --> 59:45.747
<i> I'll see who sneaks up on</i>
who this time.

59:45.749 --> 59:53.822
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

59:59.330 --> 1:00:01.863
JEREMIAH:<i> Turn back. Go home.</i>

1:00:01.865 --> 1:00:03.098
BLACKJACK:
Under whose authority?

1:00:03.100 --> 1:00:05.300
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i> JEREMIAH: Mine.

1:00:05.302 --> 1:00:08.704
The Marshal done warned you
with his mouth.<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

1:00:08.706 --> 1:00:12.374
Now I'm warning you with my gun.

1:00:12.376 --> 1:00:14.810
BLACKJACK: It's just you, huh?

1:00:14.812 --> 1:00:17.679
Look at you sittin' there all
fancy pointin' your pistol

1:00:17.681 --> 1:00:22.384
at me while The Saint
runs free starving my kids.

1:00:22.386 --> 1:00:24.086
Raiding my land.

1:00:24.088 --> 1:00:25.354
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:00:25.356 --> 1:00:26.989
I'm gonna count to three.

1:00:26.991 --> 1:00:29.891
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:00:29.893 --> 1:00:31.293
One...

1:00:31.295 --> 1:00:35.263
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:00:35.265 --> 1:00:36.665
Two...

1:00:36.667 --> 1:00:39.668
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

1:00:39.670 --> 1:00:42.704
<i> [SPITS]</i>

1:00:42.706 --> 1:00:45.040
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

1:00:45.042 --> 1:00:46.208
Three.

1:00:46.210 --> 1:00:48.644
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:00:48.646 --> 1:00:51.980
<i> [GUNSHOTS, BIRDS SQUAWKING]</i>

1:00:51.982 --> 1:00:53.915
<i> ¶ [SOMBER MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:00:53.917 --> 1:00:56.985
<i> [THUD]</i>

1:00:56.987 --> 1:00:58.687
<i> Grab his horse.</i>

1:00:58.689 --> 1:01:01.023
<i>We'll get to the Abington Ranch</i>
before sundown.

1:01:01.025 --> 1:01:03.792
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:01:03.794 --> 1:01:06.228
<i> [BLACKJACK LAUGHING,</i>
RIDING AWAY]

1:01:08.265 --> 1:01:09.765
There ya go.

1:01:09.767 --> 1:01:11.199
The Saint's gonna get you!

1:01:11.201 --> 1:01:13.935
<i> [PUNCH, THUD]</i>

1:01:13.937 --> 1:01:15.237
No, he's not.

1:01:15.239 --> 1:01:17.072
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:01:17.074 --> 1:01:18.707
<i> [DOOR CREAKS OPEN]</i>
VIRGIL: Watch her.

1:01:18.709 --> 1:01:21.710
<i> Make sure she doesn't move.</i>

1:01:21.712 --> 1:01:23.211
<i> [DOOR CLOSES]</i>

1:01:23.213 --> 1:01:29.351
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:01:29.353 --> 1:01:33.388
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:01:33.390 --> 1:01:34.890
Hey, John!

1:01:34.892 --> 1:01:36.258
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:01:36.260 --> 1:01:38.093
What?

1:01:38.095 --> 1:01:41.229
I'm giving you the one last
chance you once gave me.

1:01:41.231 --> 1:01:46.201
<i> You can leave here now,</i>
and I'll let you go.

1:01:46.203 --> 1:01:48.070
JOHN: With you in tow?

1:01:48.072 --> 1:01:51.206
<i> [JOHN COCKS GUN]</i>
VIRGIL: You're a stubborn man.

1:01:51.208 --> 1:01:53.842
Yep.

1:01:53.844 --> 1:01:56.311
<i> [DOOR CREAKS OPEN]</i>
VIRGIL: So what'll it be?

1:01:56.313 --> 1:01:59.848
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:01:59.850 --> 1:02:01.349
I'll wait.

1:02:01.351 --> 1:02:03.318
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:02:03.320 --> 1:02:05.454
To meet your maker?

1:02:05.456 --> 1:02:06.988
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:02:06.990 --> 1:02:08.724
Maybe.

1:02:08.726 --> 1:02:12.094
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:02:12.096 --> 1:02:16.765
<i> [RETREATING FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:02:16.767 --> 1:02:19.735
<i> [DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]</i>

1:02:25.743 --> 1:02:27.743
CAL:
If we're gonna meet our maker...

1:02:27.745 --> 1:02:30.278
it's not gonna be
from starvation.

1:02:30.280 --> 1:02:33.448
<i> We've got their provisions,</i>
take a look.

1:02:37.020 --> 1:02:41.957
JOHN: Looks like a dadgum
general store in here let's eat!

1:02:41.959 --> 1:02:43.525
<i> [APPLES CRUNCHING]</i>

1:02:43.527 --> 1:02:45.494
<i> [PACING FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:02:45.496 --> 1:02:47.362
VIRGIL:<i> John Breaker.</i>

1:02:47.364 --> 1:02:48.797
TUCKER: Look, why don't
we just run?

1:02:48.799 --> 1:02:50.198
<i> They ain't gonna catch us!</i>

1:02:50.200 --> 1:02:51.299
VIRGIL:
Because of what's in the barn.

1:02:51.301 --> 1:02:52.467
There's always more loot, boss.

1:02:52.469 --> 1:02:55.170
Not the loot... Breaker!

1:02:55.172 --> 1:02:57.773
TUCKER: We can get away and
regroup and gather more men.

1:02:57.775 --> 1:02:59.341
This ends<i> today.</i>

1:02:59.343 --> 1:03:01.543
I don't see no point in going
out there to die.

1:03:01.545 --> 1:03:03.845
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:03:03.847 --> 1:03:05.914
Do you wanna spend your life
lookin' over your shoulder?

1:03:05.916 --> 1:03:13.054
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:03:13.056 --> 1:03:14.456
You ready?

1:03:14.458 --> 1:03:15.857
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

1:03:15.859 --> 1:03:17.192
Aye.

1:03:17.194 --> 1:03:18.894
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:03:18.896 --> 1:03:21.396
VIRGIL: If she moves, kill her.
<i> [DOOR OPENS]</i>

1:03:21.398 --> 1:03:23.365
<i> STACEY: You got it, boss.</i>
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:03:23.367 --> 1:03:25.467
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:03:25.469 --> 1:03:27.369
<i> [APPLE THUDS]</i>

1:03:35.179 --> 1:03:38.446
JOHN: Hey, hey... what is that?

1:03:40.951 --> 1:03:43.051
<i> Uh-huh.</i>

1:03:43.053 --> 1:03:45.320
Is she pretty as your mama?

1:03:45.322 --> 1:03:47.255
She's beautiful.

1:03:49.426 --> 1:03:52.194
You live a dangerous life son,
is she okay with that?

1:03:52.196 --> 1:03:53.228
Yeah, she's fine.

1:03:53.230 --> 1:03:55.897
<i> [BITING, CRUNCHING]</i>

1:03:55.899 --> 1:03:57.199
<i> [APPLE THUDS]</i>

1:03:57.201 --> 1:03:58.333
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:03:58.335 --> 1:04:01.136
Well.

1:04:01.138 --> 1:04:03.572
We both know that mom
is a strong woman...

1:04:05.876 --> 1:04:11.413
but my life and my choices
haven't always been easy on her.

1:04:11.415 --> 1:04:14.082
A lot of late nights wonderin'
if I was comin' home on a saddle

1:04:14.084 --> 1:04:17.586
or in a box.

1:04:17.588 --> 1:04:20.388
She's fine.

1:04:20.390 --> 1:04:23.859
VIRGIL: Cal!
[GUNSHOT, CAN DROPS]

1:04:23.861 --> 1:04:28.964
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:04:28.966 --> 1:04:29.898
<i> [BULLET SPLASHING]</i>

1:04:29.900 --> 1:04:32.300
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:04:32.302 --> 1:04:33.535
<i> [BULLETS RICOCHET]</i>

1:04:33.537 --> 1:04:36.504
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:04:36.506 --> 1:04:37.973
<i> [WATER STREAMS OUT]</i>

1:04:37.975 --> 1:04:39.140
<i> [GUN CLICKS EMPTY]</i>

1:04:39.142 --> 1:04:40.609
<i> [GUN THUDS TO GROUND]</i>

1:04:40.611 --> 1:04:42.244
<i> [RETREATING FOOTSTEPS,</i>
DOOR CLOSES]

1:04:42.246 --> 1:04:43.879
JOHN:<i> Are you alright?</i>

1:04:43.881 --> 1:04:45.146
CAL: Yeah, no holes.

1:04:45.148 --> 1:04:46.381
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:04:46.383 --> 1:04:47.983
<i> Desperation?</i>

1:04:47.985 --> 1:04:49.317
Diversion.

1:04:49.319 --> 1:04:51.119
<i> [RUNNING FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:04:51.121 --> 1:04:54.222
<i> [GUNSHOT]</i>
JOHN: Anvil's on the run.

1:04:54.224 --> 1:04:56.424
You take the back,
I'll take the front.

1:04:56.426 --> 1:04:58.560
Ready? Go!

1:04:58.562 --> 1:05:00.095
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:05:00.097 --> 1:05:01.396
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

1:05:01.398 --> 1:05:06.534
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:05:06.536 --> 1:05:07.636
<i> [ANVIL GRUNTING LOUDLY]</i>

1:05:07.638 --> 1:05:10.639
<i> [GUNSHOT, ANVIL GROANS]</i>

1:05:10.641 --> 1:05:12.641
<i> [THUD]</i>

1:05:16.647 --> 1:05:20.048
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

1:05:20.050 --> 1:05:21.650
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:05:21.652 --> 1:05:24.452
<i> [TUCKER COCKS GUN]</i>
John Breaker...

1:05:24.454 --> 1:05:28.023
the only man alive who could
give my boss the quickstep.

1:05:28.025 --> 1:05:30.158
Tucker Macready...

1:05:30.160 --> 1:05:32.327
don't make me shoot a musician;

1:05:32.329 --> 1:05:35.096
The world needs as
many as it can get.

1:05:35.098 --> 1:05:36.364
I believe I got you-

1:05:36.366 --> 1:05:37.699
<i> [GUNSHOT, TUCKER GROANS]</i>

1:05:37.701 --> 1:05:39.601
<i> [TUCKER FALLS TO GROUND]</i>

1:05:43.407 --> 1:05:46.341
<i> [PANTING]</i>

1:05:49.112 --> 1:05:51.046
<i> [STACEY COCKS GUN,</i>
CLEARS THROAT]

1:05:51.048 --> 1:05:53.515
<i> [CAL COCKS GUN]</i>

1:06:03.393 --> 1:06:05.427
There's always another way.

1:06:07.030 --> 1:06:09.030
Really?

1:06:09.032 --> 1:06:10.398
Always?

1:06:10.400 --> 1:06:12.300
How've you been?

1:06:14.271 --> 1:06:17.372
I've been busy.

1:06:17.374 --> 1:06:18.673
Come here.

1:06:18.675 --> 1:06:25.046
<i> ¶ [SOFT ROMANTIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:06:25.048 --> 1:06:26.214
<i> [GRUNTS]</i>

1:06:26.216 --> 1:06:27.682
TUCKER:
The Saint is gonna kill you.

1:06:27.684 --> 1:06:30.385
JOHN: I heard that one already.
<i> [PUNCHES HIM]</i>

1:06:31.121 --> 1:06:36.057
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:06:36.059 --> 1:06:43.031
<i> ¶ [SOFT ROMANTIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:06:43.033 --> 1:06:45.433
Is this your idea
of gentle justice?

1:06:45.435 --> 1:06:48.503
<i> ¶ [SOFT ROMANTIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:06:48.505 --> 1:06:51.172
Dad, hey this is the girl
I was telling you about.

1:06:51.174 --> 1:06:52.407
Stacey Snyder.

1:06:52.409 --> 1:06:54.476
<i>I've heard a lot about you, sir.</i>

1:06:54.478 --> 1:06:56.044
<i> CAL:</i>
She works for the government.

1:06:56.046 --> 1:06:57.746
Her intel is what helped us get
the warrant.

1:06:59.282 --> 1:07:02.350
And you're...
you're okay with her being a...

1:07:02.352 --> 1:07:03.284
Spy?

1:07:03.286 --> 1:07:04.219
No offense, sheriff-

1:07:04.221 --> 1:07:05.620
Deputy.

1:07:05.622 --> 1:07:07.155
STACEY: No offense.

1:07:07.157 --> 1:07:08.757
I've been working southern
celebrations

1:07:08.759 --> 1:07:12.560
and Confederate inaugurations
since before Sumter.

1:07:12.562 --> 1:07:14.763
Your mama's gonna love her!

1:07:14.765 --> 1:07:16.364
<i> ¶ [SOFT ROMANTIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:07:16.366 --> 1:07:18.133
What if I had shot her?!

1:07:18.135 --> 1:07:19.701
Now come on,
you're not gonna shoot a girl.

1:07:19.703 --> 1:07:21.169
You can hardly look at her.

1:07:21.171 --> 1:07:22.737
<i> ¶ [SOFT ROMANTIC MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:07:22.739 --> 1:07:26.207
JOHN: Alright, you two
lovebirds... let's end this.

1:07:26.209 --> 1:07:28.043
<i> The Saint's not getting</i>
away this time.

1:07:28.045 --> 1:07:34.682
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:07:34.684 --> 1:07:36.251
Alright...

1:07:36.253 --> 1:07:38.186
I'll busy him in the front.

1:07:38.188 --> 1:07:40.088
You go around left,
and come in through the back.

1:07:40.090 --> 1:07:42.190
It'll be just like Bull Run.

1:07:42.192 --> 1:07:43.491
You ready, Miss Snyder?

1:07:43.493 --> 1:07:45.193
STACEY:<i> Yep.</i> JOHN: Ready, son?

1:07:45.195 --> 1:07:46.061
CAL: Ready.

1:07:46.063 --> 1:07:47.395
Good.

1:07:47.397 --> 1:07:54.702
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:07:54.704 --> 1:07:57.305
The odds have shifted, Virgil.

1:07:57.307 --> 1:08:00.742
You're outnumbered.
How do you wanna play it?

1:08:00.744 --> 1:08:03.745
I'm glad it's you, John...
but you're gonna have to

1:08:03.747 --> 1:08:06.181
kill me this time.
<i> [COCKS PISTOL]</i>

1:08:06.183 --> 1:08:09.384
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:08:09.386 --> 1:08:15.490
<i> [GUNFIRE IN DISTANCE]</i>

1:08:15.492 --> 1:08:19.294
<i> [RUNNING FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:08:19.296 --> 1:08:21.830
<i> [WHISTLES]</i>

1:08:21.832 --> 1:08:29.337
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:08:29.339 --> 1:08:37.412
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:08:38.482 --> 1:08:40.415
<i> [JOHN AND BUGLE</i>
BOTH COCK THEIR RIFLES]

1:08:40.417 --> 1:08:48.723
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:08:48.725 --> 1:08:51.593
<i> [CHUCKLES IN RELIEF]</i>
Oh! Morning, boys.

1:08:51.595 --> 1:08:55.430
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:08:55.432 --> 1:08:57.165
Was it worth it, Virg?

1:08:57.167 --> 1:08:59.334
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:08:59.336 --> 1:09:02.337
I'm glad it's you
they sent, John.

1:09:02.339 --> 1:09:03.905
I'm not.

1:09:03.907 --> 1:09:05.807
<i> [HAT FALLS TO GROUND]</i>

1:09:05.809 --> 1:09:08.309
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

1:09:08.311 --> 1:09:09.544
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:09:09.546 --> 1:09:11.446
<i> [BAG SNAPS OPEN]</i>

1:09:11.448 --> 1:09:14.883
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:09:14.885 --> 1:09:18.186
I lost my boy, John.

1:09:18.188 --> 1:09:21.222
<i>It's got to count for something.</i>

1:09:21.224 --> 1:09:23.558
You've got a boy.

1:09:23.560 --> 1:09:25.693
You understand.

1:09:25.695 --> 1:09:27.262
<i> They'll understand.</i>

1:09:27.264 --> 1:09:29.364
You disobeyed orders.

1:09:29.366 --> 1:09:30.765
<i> You left without leave.</i>

1:09:30.767 --> 1:09:33.168
<i>You put yourself above the Army.</i>

1:09:33.170 --> 1:09:34.669
That's called desertion.

1:09:34.671 --> 1:09:35.670
It was justice!

1:09:35.672 --> 1:09:38.273
It was war!

1:09:38.275 --> 1:09:40.575
<i> How many sons did you take</i>
in Petersburg?

1:09:40.577 --> 1:09:42.944
How about Bull Run?

1:09:42.946 --> 1:09:44.279
While you were out there
trying to even the score,

1:09:44.281 --> 1:09:45.680
you put a price on all of us.

1:09:45.682 --> 1:09:46.881
Oh, it's easy for you
to talk like that.

1:09:46.883 --> 1:09:48.850
Your boy is still breathing.

1:09:48.852 --> 1:09:51.519
And you stayed the bullet
that killed mine.

1:09:51.521 --> 1:09:53.288
<i> If it had been your boy</i>
that had been buried,

1:09:53.290 --> 1:09:55.890
<i> I'd have understood.</i>

1:09:55.892 --> 1:09:57.759
CONFEDERATE SOLDIER:
<i> Help! Someone shot Timmy!</i>

1:09:57.761 --> 1:09:59.894
VIRGIL: I guess I was followed;
Your choice... fight or flight?

1:09:59.896 --> 1:10:01.629
<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

1:10:01.631 --> 1:10:03.398
CONFEDERATE SOLDIER:
They've gotta be close.

1:10:03.400 --> 1:10:04.966
Over here! I see them!

1:10:04.968 --> 1:10:07.302
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:10:07.304 --> 1:10:09.837
Go!

1:10:09.839 --> 1:10:15.276
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:10:15.278 --> 1:10:23.651
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:10:23.653 --> 1:10:28.223
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:10:28.225 --> 1:10:29.791
<i> [BULLETS DROPPING]</i>

1:10:29.793 --> 1:10:31.392
<i> [GUNSHOTS]</i>

1:10:31.394 --> 1:10:32.927
JOHN: Go, Cal! Go! [OPENS DOOR]

1:10:32.929 --> 1:10:38.299
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:10:38.301 --> 1:10:39.601
You're late.

1:10:39.603 --> 1:10:41.269
I thought you said
like Bull Run?

1:10:41.271 --> 1:10:42.704
You were late then too.

1:10:42.706 --> 1:10:45.807
VIRGIL: I'm coming out!
[KICKS DOOR OPEN]

1:10:45.809 --> 1:10:50.945
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:10:50.947 --> 1:10:54.582
It's over, Virg... let her go.

1:10:54.584 --> 1:10:57.752
You're in no position
to negotiate.

1:10:57.754 --> 1:10:59.754
You're gonna kill
an innocent girl?

1:10:59.756 --> 1:11:01.889
I'll do what I have to
to protect the Union.

1:11:01.891 --> 1:11:04.325
No, you'll do what you have to
for<i> revenge.</i>

1:11:04.327 --> 1:11:06.427
Their treachery is unforgivable!

1:11:06.429 --> 1:11:08.796
JOHN: No, you think
your son abandoning

1:11:08.798 --> 1:11:10.932
you is unforgivable.

1:11:10.934 --> 1:11:14.269
You think the war taking your
other boy is unforgivable.

1:11:14.271 --> 1:11:16.437
Put your guns down!
<i> [COCKS PISTOL]</i>

1:11:16.439 --> 1:11:18.539
- I'll shoot her.
- You're not gonna shoot her
Virg.

1:11:18.541 --> 1:11:19.707
She doesn't deserve it.

1:11:19.709 --> 1:11:21.876
<i> [COCKS PISTOL, ABBY WHIMPERS]</i>

1:11:21.878 --> 1:11:26.314
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:11:26.316 --> 1:11:33.921
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:11:33.923 --> 1:11:36.057
You're broken...

1:11:36.059 --> 1:11:38.493
and you're bad...

1:11:38.495 --> 1:11:40.061
but you ain't evil, Virg.

1:11:40.063 --> 1:11:42.964
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:11:42.966 --> 1:11:44.599
Let her go.

1:11:44.601 --> 1:11:47.635
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:11:47.637 --> 1:11:50.004
You're right.

1:11:50.006 --> 1:11:51.773
<i> I won't shoot her.</i>

1:11:51.775 --> 1:11:54.475
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:11:54.477 --> 1:11:55.543
<i> [SHOOTS GUN AT CAL]</i>

1:11:55.545 --> 1:11:57.312
<i> [CAL GROANS]</i>

1:11:57.314 --> 1:12:00.515
VIRGIL: Drop it! Drop it!
The traitor too!

1:12:00.517 --> 1:12:03.484
<i>[SETS GUN ON GROUND] Good girl.</i>

1:12:03.486 --> 1:12:04.719
Put your gun down.

1:12:04.721 --> 1:12:06.020
Put your gun down!

1:12:06.022 --> 1:12:11.025
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:12:11.027 --> 1:12:12.860
<i> [SETS GUN ON TABLE]</i>

1:12:12.862 --> 1:12:17.398
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:12:17.400 --> 1:12:19.834
A son for a son.

1:12:19.836 --> 1:12:21.703
Now you know what it feels like.

1:12:21.705 --> 1:12:23.438
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:12:23.440 --> 1:12:25.573
Cal!

1:12:25.575 --> 1:12:28.843
Take it easy... easy.
Are you okay?

1:12:28.845 --> 1:12:32.547
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:12:32.549 --> 1:12:34.649
BLACKJACK: Howdy.<i> [COCKS RIFLE]</i>

1:12:34.651 --> 1:12:36.384
<i> [SPITS]</i>

1:12:36.386 --> 1:12:42.957
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:12:42.959 --> 1:12:44.826
We's here for a reckonin'.

1:12:44.828 --> 1:12:48.062
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:12:48.064 --> 1:12:51.032
Ah, ah, ah... drop it.

1:12:51.034 --> 1:12:57.772
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:12:57.774 --> 1:12:59.440
<i> [GUN THUDS]</i>

1:12:59.442 --> 1:13:00.475
JOHN: Cal, keep your
finger in it.

1:13:00.477 --> 1:13:01.709
We don't want ya to bleed out.

1:13:01.711 --> 1:13:04.011
<i> [LABORED BREATHING]</i>
Dad, I'm fine.

1:13:04.013 --> 1:13:09.083
<i> [LABORED BREATHING]</i>

1:13:09.085 --> 1:13:10.551
Stay with him.

1:13:10.553 --> 1:13:11.819
<i> [SPINNING GUN CHAMBER]</i> What?

1:13:11.821 --> 1:13:13.454
I said stay with him.

1:13:13.456 --> 1:13:16.891
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:13:16.893 --> 1:13:19.460
<i> Where is he?</i>

1:13:19.462 --> 1:13:20.128
<i> [JOHN KICKS VIRGIL]</i>

1:13:20.130 --> 1:13:21.829
Ah!<i> [THUD]</i>

1:13:21.831 --> 1:13:25.032
BLACKJACK: Whoa now.
That man is ours, sheriff.

1:13:25.034 --> 1:13:27.001
JOHN: I've got a warrant
for this man's arrest.

1:13:27.003 --> 1:13:28.970
<i> [VIRGIL PUNCHES, JOHN GROANS]</i>

1:13:28.972 --> 1:13:31.839
<i> [VIRGIL PUNCHING]</i>

1:13:31.841 --> 1:13:39.480
<i> [JOHN GROANING]</i>

1:13:39.482 --> 1:13:40.748
<i>[JOHN KICKING, VIRGIL GROANING]</i>

1:13:40.750 --> 1:13:43.151
CLETUS: Oh, that had to hurt!

1:13:44.854 --> 1:13:51.626
<i> [PUNCHING, GROANING]</i>

1:13:51.628 --> 1:13:52.860
Oh!<i> [THUD]</i>

1:13:52.862 --> 1:13:54.595
<i> [GROANING]</i>

1:13:54.597 --> 1:13:57.865
<i> ¶ </i> ¶

1:13:57.867 --> 1:14:00.468
<i> [PUNCHING]</i>

1:14:00.470 --> 1:14:02.136
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:14:02.138 --> 1:14:04.005
BLACKJACK:
Alright, let's wrap it up, boys.

1:14:04.007 --> 1:14:07.141
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:14:07.143 --> 1:14:08.810
<i> [PUNCHING]</i>

1:14:08.812 --> 1:14:10.178
<i> [KNEEING]</i>

1:14:10.180 --> 1:14:12.213
BLACKJACK:
I said he's ours, sheriff.

1:14:12.215 --> 1:14:15.683
<i> [GRUNTING, KNEEING]</i>

1:14:15.685 --> 1:14:17.218
<i> [THUD]</i>

1:14:17.220 --> 1:14:18.953
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:14:18.955 --> 1:14:20.521
<i> [SWATS KNIFE TO GROUND]</i>

1:14:20.523 --> 1:14:25.026
<i> [BOTH PANTING]</i>

1:14:25.028 --> 1:14:27.562
Do it!

1:14:27.564 --> 1:14:29.063
Kill me.

1:14:29.065 --> 1:14:32.166
BLACKJACK: Dead or alive,
it don't matter to us.

1:14:32.168 --> 1:14:35.136
VIRGIL: You heard 'em...
kill me!

1:14:35.138 --> 1:14:38.673
John, kill me.<i> [PANTING]</i>

1:14:38.675 --> 1:14:42.143
<i> [BIRDS CAWING]</i>

1:14:42.145 --> 1:14:43.911
I shot your son.

1:14:43.913 --> 1:14:45.913
<i> [COCKS GUN]</i>

1:14:45.915 --> 1:14:52.753
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:14:52.755 --> 1:14:55.089
So this is it?

1:14:55.091 --> 1:14:58.192
Hang a man for avenging his son?

1:14:58.194 --> 1:15:00.194
JOHN: Well, from where I'm
standing you get two

1:15:00.196 --> 1:15:04.131
choices... the reckoning,
or the redemption.

1:15:05.235 --> 1:15:07.168
The reckoning?

1:15:07.170 --> 1:15:10.571
The reckoning is what that Reb
got for murdering my boy.

1:15:10.573 --> 1:15:12.874
Well let me tell you what
redemption looks like...

1:15:12.876 --> 1:15:15.676
I never found you,
and I never see you again.

1:15:15.678 --> 1:15:18.813
<i> You go West and you start</i>
yourself a new life, Virgil.

1:15:18.815 --> 1:15:21.516
I'll give it to ya
if you'll take it.

1:15:21.518 --> 1:15:23.618
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:15:23.620 --> 1:15:24.986
So you're judge and jury?

1:15:24.988 --> 1:15:26.888
JOHN:<i> And executioner.</i>

1:15:26.890 --> 1:15:28.523
They told me don't bother
bringing you back,

1:15:28.525 --> 1:15:32.193
just find a tree and drop you.

1:15:32.195 --> 1:15:34.962
<i> But I know something</i>
they don't...

1:15:34.964 --> 1:15:38.666
you deserted,
but you're not a deserter.

1:15:38.668 --> 1:15:39.967
You're just selfish.

1:15:39.969 --> 1:15:42.270
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:15:42.272 --> 1:15:47.108
So... there's two roads.

1:15:47.110 --> 1:15:49.176
The easy one is the reckoning.

1:15:49.178 --> 1:15:50.945
The right one is redemption.

1:15:50.947 --> 1:15:53.014
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:15:53.016 --> 1:15:54.615
What's it gonna be, Virg?

1:15:54.617 --> 1:16:01.556
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:16:01.558 --> 1:16:04.825
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:16:04.827 --> 1:16:08.162
<i> [PANTING]</i>

1:16:08.164 --> 1:16:16.137
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:16:16.139 --> 1:16:18.172
JOHN: You're under arrest.

1:16:18.174 --> 1:16:19.874
The court will decide your fate.

1:16:19.876 --> 1:16:21.876
Mercy?!

1:16:21.878 --> 1:16:26.280
I spared you once because of
pity... mercy?

1:16:26.282 --> 1:16:28.683
<i> [PUNCH, THUD]</i>

1:16:28.685 --> 1:16:30.017
<i> [PANTING]</i>

1:16:30.019 --> 1:16:33.187
Ain't nothin' gentle
about mercy.

1:16:33.189 --> 1:16:36.257
Go on, I'm taking him in.

1:16:36.259 --> 1:16:39.360
BLACKJACK: You're outside your
jurisdiction, sheriff.

1:16:39.362 --> 1:16:41.596
You ain't nothin' but
a man outgunned.

1:16:41.598 --> 1:16:45.132
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:16:45.134 --> 1:16:47.969
You're on the wrong side
of justice, boys.

1:16:47.971 --> 1:16:50.938
Don't test me; Not today.

1:16:50.940 --> 1:16:52.740
BLACKJACK: Oh yeah?
Whatcha gonna do?

1:16:52.742 --> 1:16:56.978
Huh? Forgive us if
we don't oblige... come on.

1:16:56.980 --> 1:16:59.013
Oh, I'll forgive ya...

1:16:59.015 --> 1:17:01.048
<i> after I'm done with ya.</i>

1:17:06.723 --> 1:17:10.891
Heh... us versus you?

1:17:10.893 --> 1:17:12.893
Andthem. [HORSE NEIGHING]

1:17:12.895 --> 1:17:16.030
<i> [HOOF BEATS APPROACHING]</i>

1:17:16.032 --> 1:17:20.701
<i>I got no problem taking you too.</i>

1:17:20.703 --> 1:17:23.638
<i> The choice is yours.</i>

1:17:23.640 --> 1:17:25.840
BLACKJACK: Hyah!
JOHN: That's what I thought.

1:17:25.842 --> 1:17:32.113
<i> [HOOF BEATS]</i>

1:17:32.115 --> 1:17:35.282
<i> [BUGLE'S HORSE NEIGHING]</i>

1:17:35.284 --> 1:17:38.719
It's about time.

1:17:38.721 --> 1:17:42.023
BUGLE: Most men wouldn't
make it 'til dawn.

1:17:42.025 --> 1:17:45.760
Well thankfully,
you ain't most men.

1:17:45.762 --> 1:17:48.396
They shot a Deputy Marshal
on the road.

1:17:48.398 --> 1:17:51.198
<i> Do you want me to ride</i>
after them?

1:17:51.200 --> 1:17:52.933
Send the boys.

1:17:52.935 --> 1:17:54.702
Cal's been hit.

1:17:54.704 --> 1:17:58.406
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:17:58.408 --> 1:18:00.875
Get up.

1:18:00.877 --> 1:18:02.977
JOHN: Whoa. [ABBY COCKS PISTOL]

1:18:02.979 --> 1:18:05.980
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:18:05.982 --> 1:18:07.748
Hold off.

1:18:07.750 --> 1:18:08.883
Move!

1:18:08.885 --> 1:18:10.184
Not like this.

1:18:10.186 --> 1:18:13.287
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:18:13.289 --> 1:18:15.056
I said not like this.

1:18:15.058 --> 1:18:18.359
<i> [ABBY WHIMPERING]</i>
My father... my brother...

1:18:20.997 --> 1:18:21.996
Abby-

1:18:21.998 --> 1:18:23.431
You spared him!

1:18:23.433 --> 1:18:25.366
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:18:25.368 --> 1:18:29.737
Shh, he's going to court, Abby.
And this time he'll hang.

1:18:29.739 --> 1:18:31.105
<i> ¶ [TENSE MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:18:31.107 --> 1:18:33.307
Not this time.

1:18:37.346 --> 1:18:41.816
<i> [ABBY CRYING]</i>

1:18:41.818 --> 1:18:45.152
JOHN: Take him away, boys.

1:18:45.154 --> 1:18:46.821
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:18:46.823 --> 1:18:50.991
<i> [ABBY CRYING]</i>

1:18:53.262 --> 1:18:55.863
<i> [FLASHBACK:]</i> BUGLE:
He deserved to hang.

1:18:55.865 --> 1:18:57.798
I know.

1:18:57.800 --> 1:18:58.999
<i> [SLOW HOOF BEATS RETREATING]</i>

1:18:59.001 --> 1:19:01.268
<i> BUGLE: Then why didn't you?</i>

1:19:01.270 --> 1:19:04.405
If it were<i> my</i> son who
were shot and killed...

1:19:04.407 --> 1:19:07.742
I'd probably have done the same.

1:19:07.744 --> 1:19:09.176
<i> [GENTLE TAP]</i>

1:19:09.178 --> 1:19:13.514
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:19:13.516 --> 1:19:16.751
No, you wouldn't.

1:19:16.753 --> 1:19:21.088
<i> [FOOTSTEPS]</i>

1:19:21.090 --> 1:19:23.924
<i> [BIRDS CHIRPING]</i>

1:19:23.926 --> 1:19:30.965
<i> ¶ [SOFT MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:19:30.967 --> 1:19:33.400
<i> [HORSE NEIGHS]</i>

1:19:33.402 --> 1:19:34.969
<i> [CAL SHOUTING HAPPILY AT JOHN]</i>
Look at you all gussied up

1:19:34.971 --> 1:19:36.771
<i> from your court date!</i>

1:19:36.773 --> 1:19:38.172
Bugle told me the verdict.

1:19:38.174 --> 1:19:39.306
JOHN: Umm-hmm.

1:19:39.308 --> 1:19:41.308
I got you this as a reminder...

1:19:41.310 --> 1:19:42.510
it's a little less morbid.

1:19:42.512 --> 1:19:47.782
<i> ¶ [SOFT MUSIC] ¶</i>

1:19:47.784 --> 1:19:50.484
I like it.

1:19:50.486 --> 1:19:52.353
BONNIE: You sure you don't wanna
stay a while longer?

1:19:52.355 --> 1:19:54.255
CAL: Well, I gotta get back to
Washington,

1:19:54.257 --> 1:19:56.056
and report on The Saint's trial.

1:19:56.058 --> 1:19:59.293
<i> [SARCASTICALLY]</i>
Back to Washington.

1:19:59.295 --> 1:20:01.862
We're proud of you.

1:20:01.864 --> 1:20:03.831
We did it.

1:20:03.833 --> 1:20:05.833
Yes we did.

1:20:05.835 --> 1:20:07.535
And it was a pleasure
getting to know you.

1:20:07.537 --> 1:20:09.570
The pleasure was mine, sheriff.

1:20:11.340 --> 1:20:13.207
- Dad.
- What?

1:20:13.209 --> 1:20:15.242
<i> [GASPS]</i>

1:20:15.244 --> 1:20:16.443
Wait what?

1:20:16.445 --> 1:20:18.979
BONNIE: Keep us posted!
JOHN: A wedding?

1:20:18.981 --> 1:20:21.115
Don't wait too long.
Campaign season's coming.

1:20:21.117 --> 1:20:22.383
CAL: What are you gonna do?
Run against me?

1:20:22.385 --> 1:20:23.918
JOHN:
Oh, I ought to just to have the

1:20:23.920 --> 1:20:26.220
pleasure of ordering
you around again.

1:20:26.222 --> 1:20:28.055
Dad, you'll always be above my

1:20:28.057 --> 1:20:29.890
rank in this county.

1:20:29.892 --> 1:20:34.094
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:20:34.096 --> 1:20:35.496
BONNIE: You take care of him.

1:20:35.498 --> 1:20:37.131
STACEY:
We take care of each other.

1:20:37.133 --> 1:20:45.206
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:20:45.942 --> 1:20:47.541
<i> [HORSE NEIGHING]</i>

1:20:47.543 --> 1:20:51.145
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:20:51.147 --> 1:20:52.880
<i> [EXHALES]</i>

1:20:52.882 --> 1:21:00.955
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:21:02.525 --> 1:21:06.093
BUGLE, V/O:<i> There's a fight</i>
inside of men as well.

1:21:06.095 --> 1:21:08.195
<i> A fight against a reckoning.</i>

1:21:08.197 --> 1:21:10.564
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:21:10.566 --> 1:21:14.268
<i> A reckoning of all the</i>
things we've done...

1:21:14.270 --> 1:21:16.136
<i> or didn't do.</i>

1:21:16.138 --> 1:21:18.305
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:21:18.307 --> 1:21:20.608
<i> My granddaddy...</i>

1:21:20.610 --> 1:21:22.309
<i> he called it a warrant.</i>

1:21:22.311 --> 1:21:24.578
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:21:24.580 --> 1:21:27.248
<i> And he warns that</i>
at some point...

1:21:27.250 --> 1:21:29.183
<i> it hunts after us all.</i>

1:21:29.185 --> 1:21:31.252
<i> ¶ ¶</i>

1:21:31.254 --> 1:21:34.388
<i> Sometimes to reckon...</i>

1:21:34.390 --> 1:21:34.421
<i> always to redeem.</i>
